title: mega brownies
directions: Mix according to package directions.
Fold in the rest of the ingredients and bake according to package directions.
Pan will be heavy.
Brownies will be moist.

title: cinnamon-spiced peaches
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium nonstick skillet; stir well.
Cover and cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until peaches are tender.
Serve as a fruit side dish, a sauce for fat-free pound cake, angel food cake or low-fat vanilla ice cream or an accompaniment to ham or roast pork.

title: red velvet cake
directions: For cake coloring, I pour this in the cup with my oil and wrinch out bottle with water as part of the water.
Beat all up and pour into 3 well-greased 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: frozen corn
directions: Mix and put in freezer.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken, in a saucepan. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Wash and dry chicken and place in baking dish.
Pour half or all of the barbecue sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 50 to 60 minutes, basting with remaining sauce every 15 minutes.

title: best baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and stir with a spoon until thoroughly mixed.
Spray a 2-quart casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour beans into dish.
Lay raw bacon strips on top of bean mixture to cover entirely.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Decrease temperature to 300° and bake 2 more hours.

title: creamed broccoli soup
directions: Bring vegetables to a boil in the chicken stock.
Add salt and simmer until tender.
Cool.
Place in a blender.
Add cream and pepper.
Blend until smooth and creamy.
Pour back into pan and add potato soup; mix well.
Heat until hot; add cheese in chunks, stirring on low heat until the cheese melts.
Serve garnished with lemon slices.
Can be frozen.

title: yogurt cups
directions: You will need four 6-ounce custard cups (ungreased).

title: tomato basil soup
directions: Combine tomatoes and juice in saucepan.
Simmer 30 minutes over low to medium heat.
Cool slightly and place in blender or food processor.
Add basil and process to puree.
This will have to be done in batches.
Return to saucepan.
Add cream and butter. Stir over low heat until butter and cream are incorporated.
Stir in salt and pepper before serving.
Garnish with more fresh basil. Serves 8.

title: orange roughy parmesan
directions: Place fillets in single layer in buttered baking dish.
Brush with lemon juice and let stand for 10 minutes.

Combine cheese, butter, mayonnaise, green onion, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce. Broil fillets 3 to 4 inches under preheated broiler for 5 minutes. Spread with cheese mixture and broil for an additional 2 to 3 minutes.
Watch carefully!
Sole or any other fresh, white fish can be substituted for orange roughy.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot apple cider punch
directions: Put liquids in bottom of 22 cup percolator.
Combine other ingredients in basket and perk.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown beef and onion; pour off fat.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
In a 2-quart dish, layer noodles, meat, sauce, cheese mixture and cheese.
End with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: orange roughy in citrus sauce(low-fat)
directions: Place fish in non-metal baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients except marmalade and cornstarch.
Mix to dissolve orange juice concentrate.
Reserve 1/2 cup for sauce.
Pour remaining mixture over fish.
Cover fish and marinate in refrigerator at least 45 minutes.
Turn at least once.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Pour mixture over top of meat in pan and mix well.
Top with Mozzarella cheese slices.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts, about 1/2 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.
Cream 2 sticks of margarine.
Add powdered sugar and eggs.
Beat for 15 minutes. Spread mixture over crust.
Cover with pineapple.
Layer with sliced bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate.
Serves 15 to 18.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil, water and frosting in mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour or until brown.
Cool in pan 30 minutes before turning out cake.

title: minestrone milan style
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
In large pot saute in hot oil, garlic, onion and fresh vegetables for 10 minutes.
Stir; add rice, beans, salt, pepper and bean stock.
Cover; simmer until beans and rice are tender and most of soup has been absorbed. This usually takes about 1 1/2 hours.
Add cheese and mix thoroughly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Stir every 2 minutes.
With a mixer, mix in chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Pour into a greased pan and cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine butter, egg, bananas and buttermilk; mix until smooth, then add dry ingredients and nuts.
Place in an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, then spread into a baking dish. Crush cornflakes over mixture so that no potatoes are showing. Squeeze butter over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Slice or dice the beets; set aside.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water and boil for 5 minutes.
Add beets and simmer 1/2 hour.
Add butter and season with salt and pepper.
Serves 6 to 8 persons.
Great with pork.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown the onion and ground beef.
Drain.
Mix the the tomato sauce, bread crumbs, oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
Place in unbaked deep dish pie shell.

title: macaroons
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Bake on waxed paper on ungreased cookie sheet at 250° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: million dollar cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with pie filling.
Mix sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and milk.
Pour over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Wrap chicken in bacon strips; secure with toothpicks.
Line casserole with chipped beef; lay chicken breasts on this.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over breasts.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cook at 300° for 2 hours or until done.
Serves 12.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening; add eggs, vanilla and soda in water.
Blend well.
Add flour, oats, cereal, nuts and coconut and stir until well mixed.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Cool, remove chicken from bones.
Break, bread. In bowl, add all ingredients together.
Add dash of sage.
Also add chicken broth; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan and bake in 350° oven for 40 or 50 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry and cherry pie
directions: Mix
cherry pie filling with strawberries. Fill pie shells and cover with pie shell. Bake 425° oven until golden brown.

title: ranger cookies(awesome and chewy)
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add and mix next 2 ingredients. Sift and add next 4 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Variations:
Oatmeal or 3 tablespoons liver powder or wheat germ.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Place cooked macaroni, cheese, salt and pepper in alternate layers in buttered, large baking dish, ending with cheese.
Pour milk over.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: peanut butter fudge(microwave)
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter in a 3-quart mixing bowl.
Cook on Full power for 10 to 13 minutes.
Stir 3 times during cooking time. Beat in the marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla until creamy. Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Cool.
Combine with other ingredients.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Mix egg and water (do not beat).
Add pecans and stir.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon separately and then mix with pecans.
Bake on buttered foil for 30 minutes at 325°, stirring several times.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken; remove from bone and chop into small pieces. Set aside.
Mix soup and sour cream together; set aside.
Cover bottom of dish lightly with soup mixture.
Lay flat each tortilla, pieces of chicken, sprinkle of green onions and grated cheese. Roll up like a jelly roll.
Place each tortilla, seam side down, in an oblong Pyrex dish.
When all tortillas are in dish, spread remaining soup and sour cream mixture over tortillas and then remaining grated cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: miner's breakfast
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add potatoes and pepper and brown slightly.
Add garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour eggs over potatoes and cook until eggs form soft curds, stirring constantly.
Mix in crumbled bacon.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Place skillet in oven or under broiler until cheese is melted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: meat and vegetable pie
directions: Brown ground chuck in skillet.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add garlic salt, chopped onion and peppers.
Cook until onions and peppers are steamed.
Drain string beans.
Add to meat mixture on low heat; steam about 10 minutes.

title: faye's fudge
directions: Melt chips in double boiler. Add milk and mix well. Chill and cut into pieces.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Slice onions into thick slices.
Soak in ice water for about 15 minutes.
Drain and coat with flour.
Dip in eggs and then in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: snickers cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and pour half the batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. While baking, melt together the caramels, milk and margarine.

When cake has cooked first 20 minutes, cool 10 minutes, then pour caramel mixture on top. Reduce oven to 250°. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top of caramel mixture. Cover with remaining cake batter.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes.
Replace oven to 350° and bake 10 minutes or until done.

title: rice pilau casserole
directions: Start oven at moderate (350°). Grease 2-quart casserole.
Cook rice until tender, according to package directions, and all water is absorbed.
Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Saute chicken livers 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add mushrooms and their liquid, soup, milk, pepper, parsley and wine.
Cook until hot and smooth.
Mix with rice. Pour into prepared casserole.
Top with nuts.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: golden anniversary punch
directions: Blend pineapple and its juice, one can at a time, 15 to 20 seconds or until thick.
To pineapple, add undiluted lemonade and sugar and mix well.
Stir in club soda.
Add ice cubes.
Makes about 10 cups or 20 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion and pepper in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Combine in bowl with chopped chicken and green chili peppers.
Set aside.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Blend flour, coriander and salt using wire whisk.
Stir in chicken broth.
Cook and stir until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream and 1/2 cup Monterey Jack cheese.
Add mixture to chicken, onion and pepper mixture.
Place some of the chips in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Pour mixture over chips. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with chips, tomatoes, jalapenos and guacamole.

title: macaroni bake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked sesame-caraway potato sticks
directions: Melt butter over low heat; season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat; add potato sticks and toss to coat well.
In a shallow dish, combine seeds and roll potato sticks in the mixture. Bake potato sticks on a baking sheet at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until tender. Serves 2.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain cooked broccoli.
Combine all ingredients with broccoli, except margarine and crackers or cornflake crumbs.
Pour the ingredients in a saucepan and sprinkle the cracker crumbs or cornflakes into the margarine.
Sprinkle the margarine and crackers or cornflakes over the casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water; soften cream cheese with evaporated milk.
Add mayonnaise and whip until smooth.
Add pineapple and juice (a can of fruit cocktail makes it better and may be added if desired).

title: woodward house crab
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Add other ingredients to crab meat.
Add 1/2 cup cracker crumbs, 1 teaspoon parsley, 1/2 cup light cream (half and half), salt and pepper to crab and toss lightly.
Bake at 450° until bubbly.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix jello and fruit; put in dish. Slice bananas on top of this. Sprinkle with marshmallows. Congeal.

title: onion cheese casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam. Separate onions into rings, put layer of each into dish, then some cheese and butter. Repeat. Pour over wine or broth. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. If onion and cheese start to get brown, cover with foil.

title: crab bites
directions: Cut crusts off bread.
Roll thin with rolling pin.
Melt 1/3 cup oleo.
Add cheese and melt.
Flake crab meat and add to mixture.
Spread on bread slices, then roll in melted oleo, then sesame seed.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve, after browning on broiler.

title: chicken salsa
directions: Lightly brown chicken in frying pan.
Then place chicken in casserole dish and pour salsa over it.
Cover with aluminum foil and cook on 350 degrees for 35-45 minutes.
Serve with rice & shredded cheese.

title: june cleaver's cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour, salt and baking soda; mix well.
Mix in chocolate chips.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add beans, salt, tomatoes, ketchup and steak sauce.
Pour mixture into ungreased baking dish.
Mix cornbread and drop in spoonfuls on top of contents of baking dish. Bake at 350° until cornbread is brown (about 40 minutes).

title: special k loaf
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Press into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Melt margarine and pour it over the top of the loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Turn out of pan, slice and serve.
Serves 6 to 8. May be served with brown gravy or tomato sauce.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend all ingredients and put into pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and pepper; drain off fat.
Mix soups, cheese and rice in a bowl.
Add sausage.
Mix together and pour into a buttered casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a coffee can well.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Fill coffee can about 1/2 full. Bake for 1 hour.
Cool 5 minutes, then remove from can.
Makes about 5 loaves.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix together red food coloring, water and Quik; set aside. Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs and first mixture. Beat 2 minutes.
Add buttermilk, flour, salt and vanilla; cream for 10 minutes.
By hand, add vinegar and soda.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in greased and floured pan.

title: rice and cabbage casserole
directions: Wash, drain and coarsely shred cabbage.
Steam cabbage in oil and water for 15 minutes.
Drain and set aside.

title: ground beef stew
directions: Peel and chop potatoes, carrots and onions; cook until tender in small amount of water.
Brown beef in skillet; drain off fat. Add beef stew mix and mix well before adding to cooked vegetables. Pour in tomato juice, peas and ketchup.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Mix sour cream and soups together.
Pour over chicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste, then paprika.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for one and a half hours.

title: hankie pankies
directions: Brown sausage and beef; drain.
Reheat, adding rest of ingredients.
Spoon onto bread.
Broil until golden brown.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Beat egg whites and set aside.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each egg. Sift flour and soda together.
Add to sugar mixture alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Cook in 3 layers or sheet cake pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tom thumb cookies
directions: Cream
butter or
margarine,
brown
sugar
and
flour. Spread in 8 x 10-inch pan
that
has been greased with butter. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix
rest
of ingredients and spread over crust and bake 25 more minutes.

title: north woods wild rice soup
directions: In Dutch oven, melt butter over medium heat. Add onion, carrots and mushrooms. Cook until carrots are soft. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add broth all at once.
Cook and stir until bubbly. Stir in evaporated milk, wild rice and cream cheese. Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: bernie's crab imperial
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: trail mix
directions: Put all ingredients in a large zipper-type food storage bag. Shake mix. Enjoy!

title: brazilian shrimp pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and knead until well mixed and smooth.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Cream cheese and sour cream. Add lemonade. Add eggs and flour. Grease and flour bundt pan. Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 14 minutes.

title: braised rabbit
directions: Cut rabbit into serving pieces.
Season with salt and pepper. Lightly brown the rabbit in butter in a heavy saucepan.
Add onions, celery, parsley and soup stock or bouillon.
Cover the pot tightly; simmer the meat until it is done, about 1 1/2 hours, being careful not to let boil.
Thicken broth by adding flour and season to taste, adding Kitchen Bouquet, if desired.

title: potato wedges
directions: Slice potatoes.
Leave the peeling on.
Dip potatoes in the milk and roll in the cornmeal.
Fry in skillet until potatoes are golden brown.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender, then cut chicken into bite-size pieces. Mix sour cream, soup and chicken together. Melt butter and crumble up crackers. Mix your butter, crackers and poppy seed together. Pour half of cracker mix in bottom of bowl. Pour your chicken mixture on top, then pour remaining cracker mix on top. Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: cajun pecan catfish
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Coat a shallow baking pan with nonstick cooking spray; place fish in pan.
Combine oil, cajun seasoning, lemon juice and thyme in a small bowl.
Spoon or brush half the mixture over fish.
Add pecans, parmesan cheese, breadcrumbs and parsley to remaining oil mixture; mix well.
Spoon onto fish and spread evenly.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes (depending on thickness of fish), or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
If desired, garnish with lemon.

title: sweet vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet. Saute onions until tender and clear in color, about 15 minutes. Butter a casserole dish and line with crumbs. Layer onions, soup and cheese, lightly salting the layers of onions. Beat eggs, add milk, salt and pepper. Pour over layered onions. Sprinkle cheese and a few more cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, 35-45 minutes.

title: pecan chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening and both sugars, then add eggs, vanilla, salt, soda and water. Mix in flour. Add nuts and chocolate chips. Roll in small balls. Press flat on cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes or until light brown at 350°.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes; cook until tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Saute onion in butter in small skillet until tender. Combine potatoes, onion and the remaining ingredients in a large bowl; mix gently.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening or oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll teaspoonfuls into balls.
Roll in sugar or cinnamon and sugar.
Place on cookie sheet; flatten with a glass.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, salt, flour, soda, eggs and fruit cocktail.
Pour into greased loaf cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar, pecans and/or coconut over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs(reduced fat)
directions: In bowl combine all ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Arrange in broiler pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until slightly brown.
Prepare with Sweet-N-Sour Sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wonderful salad chinese style
directions: Mix
tomatoes,	 cucumbers,
lettuce,	etc.
Buy
rice vinegar in the
Chinese
section where you buy soy sauce, etc. If you wish, add
a
little
olive oil to your salad, but it's not needed for a very fine no-calorie dressing.

title: no peek beef
directions: Combine and cover.
Put in oven for 5 hours at 250° or 2 hours at 350°.
Serve over noodles.

title: helen depriests' baked beans
directions: Cook beans until almost done. Drain off liquid.
Add tomato sauce, dark molasses, brown sugar, mustard, bacon drippings and onion to beans.
Place in covered baking dish. Top with bacon strips. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring first 2 ingredients to a boil and remove from stove. Stir peanut butter into hot syrup. Place cereal and peanuts into a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan. Pour chocolate chips on top. Let stand 5 minutes and spread chocolate chips. Place under broiler for seconds to soften, if necessary. Put into refrigerator to set, but don't leave in for very long. Cut in squares (I don't chop peanuts).

title: lissy's sweet bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Scald milk and stir in sugar, butter and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir beaten eggs and yeast into milk mix, then beat in 2 cups of flour.
Knead in enough remaining flour to make a smooth dough which is easy to handle. Cover and let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down and cover. Rest for 10 minutes.
Divide dough in half and shape each into a round loaf.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Brush with beaten egg yolk and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Drain first 3 ingredients.
Combine with Cool Whip. Refrigerate overnight.

title: four layer dinner
directions: Microwave spinach in package on High for 3 to 4 minutes to defrost.
Drain and set aside.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Melt together brown sugar and butter.
Cut biscuits in half and coat with cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Place biscuits in a Bundt pan.
Pour butter/brown sugar mixture evenly over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Add cream cheese.
Layer with wafers, bananas, pudding mixture and Cool Whip.
Do this until Cool Whip is on top.
Top with nuts.

title: outback steakhouse coconut shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp. Dry well on paper towels and set aside. In a bowl, combine all dry ingredients for batter. Add 2 tablespoons of oil and ice water. Stir to blend.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix brown sugar, tomato sauce and mustard and set aside. Thoroughly mix meat, egg, onion, cracker crumbs, salt, pepper and 1/2 tomato mix. Form into loaf and pour remainder of tomato mix on top of loaf. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: carolina pound cake
directions: Cream shortenings; add sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add flour and milk.
Add flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool cake before removing from pan.

title: "irish" mint brownies
directions: Bake brownie mix as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat confectioners sugar, 1/2 cup butter, water, mint extract and green food coloring until smooth.
Spread this over cooled brownies in pan.
Mix 6 tablespoons butter with chocolate chips.
Melt in microwave.
Stir frequently until smooth.
Pour evenly over frosting layer on brownies.
Let cool overnight for best cutting results.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Beat all ingredients well.
Bake in greased Bundt pan or rectangle pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut a 1/2-inch slice from the top of each tomato; discard tops.
Scoop out pulp; discard seeds.
Coarsely chop pulp (should have about 1 cup).
Set aside.
In a medium skillet, cook garlic in margarine for 30 seconds.
Stir in tomato pulp, green pepper and basil.
Cook for 2 minutes or until green pepper is crisp-tender.
Stir in croutons and parsley.
Spoon crouton mixture into tomatoes.
Arrange stuffed tomatoes in a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon butter
directions: Melt butter.
Add
sugar
to butter, then add eggs plus the lemon
juice.
Cook
in a double boiler until thick, about 1/2 hour.
Do not boil.

title: baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir baked beans, onions, brown sugar, dark Karo, celery, mustard, ketchup and wieners all together.
Let stand for 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs together.
Add flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and vanilla.
Then add remaining ingredients together; mix well and drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Boil macaroni until tender; drain.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 stick margarine.
Stir until margarine has melted.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into casserole dish; spread with 1 medium can of Star-Kist tuna, then spread rest of mixture on top of tuna.
Cover top with cheese and bake until cheese is melted at 350°.

title: cherry delight
directions: Line 9-inch square pan or baking dish with whole graham crackers, breaking crackers, if needed.
Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package.
Let stand 5 minutes, then blend with Cool Whip.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Mix graham crackers, butter and 1 cup sugar.
Press almost all into greased pan (save some for the top).
Mix Dream Whip, the balance of the sugar and cream cheese.
Use half of this mixture on top of the graham cracker crust.
Spread the cherries on top of the cream cheese layer, then the balance of the cream cheese mixture on top of the cherries.
Sprinkle the rest of the graham cracker mixture on top of the cream cheese.
Keep refrigerated.

title: microwave peanut brittle(total cooking time: 18 to 22 minutes)
directions: Place sugar, corn syrup, water, salt and peanuts in 2-quart microwave-proof bowl or casserole.
Cook on High-max power for 5 minutes, then stir.
Cook on High-max power 13 to 18 minutes or until syrup separates into threads.
This is the hard-crack stage or 300° on candy thermometer.
Check temperature frequently during last few minutes.
Do not leave thermometer in oven while cooking. Stir in butter, baking soda and vanilla just until light and bubbly.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet; spread, cool and break into pieces.
Yield: about 1 1/4 pounds.

title: dump cake
directions: Empty pineapple into well-greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple.
Cut margarine into pieces and place on top.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
This cake is best cooked and refrigerated overnight.

title: josie's 9 quart relish
directions: Combine chopped (or diced) ingredients and liquids.
Add spice ball and bring to boil.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Remove spice ball, place in jars and seal or in plastic containers and freeze.

title: bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon.
Mix altogether but water and vinegar.
Heat water and vinegar to boil; stir in egg mixture.
Stir constantly until thick.
Add bacon.

title: finnish pancakes
directions: Melt butter in 450° oven in a 12 x 16 pan. Mix remaining ingredients and pour into the hot butter. Bake at 450° for 20 to 23 minutes.

title: archie's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a large bowl.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cover meat loaf with ketchup and cover with foil. Uncover for the last 20 minutes and allow to brown.

title: easy caramel frosting
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan.
Add brown sugar, stirring until smooth.
Add milk.
Boil 1 minute over low heat.
Let cool until lukewarm.
With mixer, beat in confectioners sugar until frosting is thick.
Add vanilla.

title: chicken 'n stuffing
directions: Boil chicken until tender (save broth).
Debone; cut into bite size pieces.
Place in bottom of 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with 1 cup broth and place on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: pepperoni cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in a ball.

title: ripe tomato catsup
directions: Peel tomatoes and quarter.
Add chopped onions and peppers. Add rest of ingredients; cook until thick.

title: tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well.
Roll dough thin and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: oyster dressing
directions: In large pot, mix together all ingredients.
Wet bread with oyster water and water.
Squeeze off excess water.
Mix with everything else.
In large frying pan, put 1 cup cooking oil. Heat well, then turn down heat to halfway.
Put stuffing in pan and fry for 1/2 hour until light brown, stirring constantly. Stuff bird.
Cover with foil.
Put it in oven at 350° for 5 to 6 hours.

title: brisket
directions: Soak brisket in mixture of all other ingredients for 24 hours, turning once or twice.
Bake at 300° for 4 to 5 hours.
Also good cooked over a charcoal fire.

title: lemon "cake-top" pie
directions: Stir well and add beaten egg whites last.
Place in unbaked crust in hot 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Turn down to 325° for 35 minutes.

title: double coconut cream pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine the first 1/3 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in milk and cream of coconut.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Gradually stir about 1 cup of the hot milk mixture into the beaten egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Return all of the mixture to saucepan.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine until melted.
Stir in 1 cup coconut and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Fry bacon; drain.
Saute onions in bacon grease.
Add catsup, brown sugar and water.
Bring to a boil; add drained green beans. Add crumbled bacon.
Bake for 2 to 3 hours at 325°, covered.

title: baked chicken loaf
directions: Cook chicken with onion, celery salt and pepper until chicken is tender.
If more meat is desired, cook 1/2 pound veal.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan (greased) for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with mushroom sauce or chicken gravy.

title: baked potato goo
directions: Cream all ingredients together; chill.

title: bean-pasta soup mix
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; divide evenly and place in 6 airtight plastic bags.
Add 2 tablespoons plus 1/4 teaspoon bouillon granules to each package.
Label "Herb Mix" and seal. Combine black-eyed peas and next 3 ingredients; divide evenly and place in 6 airtight plastic bags.
Label "Bean Mix" and seal. Place 1/3 cup pasta into 6 airtight plastic bags.
Label "Pasta" and seal.
Place 1 bag herb mix, 1 bag bean mix and 1 bag pasta in a gift container; repeat procedure with remaining bags.
Yield:
6 (3-bag) gifts.

title: favorite fruitcake
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs unti light.
Resift flour with baking powder, salt and spices.
Add to egg mixture alternately with rum blended with jelly and vanilla.
Stir in raisins, candied fruit and nuts.
Spoon into two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for about 2 1/2 hours.
When thoroughly cold, wrap tightly in foil and store several weeks.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut small tip off chicken wing.
Mix all ingredients together and marinate wings for 2 to 4 hours. Bake in shallow pan at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: better than nothing soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add cabbage cut in small sizes.
Add chopped onion, tomatoes, tomato sauce and beans.
Add water to desired thickness.
Season to taste with salt and pepper, soy or Worcestershire sauce.
Add bouillon cubes.
Simmer 1 hour.
Keeps good in refrigerator up to a week.

title: pumpkin bread *
directions: Blend all ingredients but flour.
Add flour.
Bake on greased and floured loaf pans (2) for 1 hour at 350° or until tester comes out dry.

title: honey butter balls
directions: Combine dry milk, honey and peanut butter in mixing bowl. Stir until mixed thoroughly.
Shape in long rolls.
Combine coconut and flakes; mix on waxed paper.
Coat rolls in coconut and flakes.
Put on waxed paper.
Shape into balls.

title: green tomato jelly
directions: Blend tomatoes.
Add sugar.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Skim off top.
Add 1 small package raspberry jello.
Let cool and store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: pepper-lime chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Broil chicken about 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: bacon-corn casserole
directions: Pour Pride corn into casserole.
Top with slices of bacon; bake at 350° until bacon is crisp and corn is heated.
Garnish with mixture of green pepper and pimento.
Yields 4 servings.

title: percolator punch
directions: Place all liquids into percolator. In bottom of percolator basket, combine sugar and spices. Allow to perk.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add enough sweet milk to make a stiff batter.
Slide by teaspoonfuls into hot deep grease and cook until done.

title: peach pickles
directions: Dip peaches into boiling water for 30 seconds to loosen skins.
Cool in cold water; drain.
Place in 4 qt bowl containing 1 1/2 T salt and 2 qts water to prevent darkening.
Drain just before using.

title: marbled orange fudge
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2 pan with the 1 1/2 tsp butter. In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, cream and remaining butter. Cook and stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved. Bring to a boil; cook while stirring for 4 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in the vanilla chips and marshmallow cream until smooth. Remove 1 cup of mixture and set aside. Add the orange extract and food colorings to remaining mixture in the saucepan, stir until blended. Pour into the prepared pan. Drop the reserved mixture by spoonfuls over the top; cut through mixtures with a knife to swirl. Cover and refrigerate until set. Cut into squares. Yield about 2 1/2 lb.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Mix cocoa and water in large saucepan.
Use a large saucepan or it will boil over.
Heat and stir to dissolve cocoa.
Add sugar, stir until dissolved.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour into sterilized pint jar, store covered in refrigerator.
Keeps for several weeks.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Heat oven to 450° (hot).
Roll biscuit dough only 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into oblong pieces, 4 x 3-inches.
Roll each piece around a wiener or frankfurter, letting tip show at each end. Seal well by pinching edge of dough into roll.
Bake with sealed edge underneath, about 15 minutes.
Serve hot with mustard, catsup or relishes.
Makes 10 to 12.

title: herbed liver
directions: Combine margarine and lemon juice in custard cup.
Put cup in hot water and simmer until margarine melts.
Add herbs and set aside.
Sprinkle liver with salt and pepper and put in greased baking dish.
Broil five inches from source of heat for 3 minutes until liver is browned.
Turn and brown other side.
Pour margarine mixture over liver.
Broil 1 more minute.
Serve.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over a graham cracker crust made of graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Put into 2 (9-inch) pie pans (shell). Cook in 300° oven as long as
it
takes to get done.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Brown onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add paste and 2 cans of water; simmer for 30 minutes.
Cut eggplant into thin slices.
Place in salt water for 1 hour.
Rinse and drain.
Fry eggplant until brown on both sides.
Layer sauce, eggplant and cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Freeze through.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: magic cherry cobbler
directions: Cream all together and pour batter in pan.
Top with 1 can cherries and spoon 1/4 cup sugar on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Stir altogether and pour in an 8 x 12-inch casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brandy slush
directions: Mix 7 cups water and sugar and bring to a boil.
Let cool. Boil 2 cups water and tea bags; let cool.
Combine lemonade, orange juice and brandy in ice cream bucket.
Mix all together and freeze.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: To prepare a cup of fresh persimmon pulp, force soft, ripe skinned persimmons through a strainer or ricer. Mix together pulp, sugar, milk, butter and vanilla.

title: sourdough chocolate cake
directions: Combine sourdough starter, flour, nonfat dry milk and water; mix.
Cover and let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Cream shortening.
Over shortening, sift sugar, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each.
Add sourdough mixture to creamed mixture.
Stir in semi-sweet or unsweetened chocolate (melted and cooled).
Mix well.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and milk alternately. Stir in vanilla.
Save 1/2 cup batter to add to icing.
Bake in lightly greased tube pan at 300° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: taco soup
directions: Add more pinto beans, if desired.
Do not drain juices.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream of asparagus soup(makes 6 cups of soup)
directions: Place asparagus and celery in 1/4 teaspoon salt and boiling water just to cover.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Reserve 1 cup of juice.

title: ranch cheese ball
directions: Prepare Ranch dressing mix with milk and mayonnaise.
Mix prepared salad dressing and cream cheese.
Add Cheddar cheese. Cover and freeze for 30 minutes.
Shape and roll in almonds.

title: rum cake
directions: Before you start, sample the rum and check for quality.
Good, isn't it?
Now, go ahead, select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc. and check the rum again for quality.
It must be just right.
Try it again.
With an electric mixer beat 1 cup butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and beat again; meanwhile, make certain that the rum is of the finest quality.
Add 2 large eggs and 2 cups of fried fruit and beat until very high. If the fruit gets stuck in the beaters, just pry it loose with a screwdriver.
Sample the rum again, checking for consistency. Next, sift in 3 cups of baking powder and a pinch of rum, 1 teaspoon toda and 1 cup pepper or salt.
Anyway, fon't dret.
Just tample the rum again and mix in 1/2 pint of lemon luice.
Fold in chopped buttermilk and the strained nuts.
Tample tum again.
Now 1 bablespoon srown bugar, or whatever color is available.
Mix well, grease oven and curn on the take pan to 350°.
Pour the whole mess in the oven.
Cake tum rake out after mifty finutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
Moisten with milk.
Press out excess milk.
Mix with remaining ingredients and shape into cakes. Fry until brown.

title: 9 layer salad
directions: Layer in a bowl the first 7 ingredients.
Refrigerate. Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.
Crumble the bacon over the salad.
Place the eggs and tomatoes over the salad.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Grease pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onions.
Drain. Stir in taco sauce.
Spread in pie plate.
Top with chilies.
Beat Bisquick, milk and eggs until smooth, about 1 minute.
Pour over meat.
Bake 25 minutes. Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes and lettuce, if desired.

title: margaret's molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in a saucepan over low heat; let cool.
In large bowl combine shortening, sugar, molasses and egg; beat well. Sift together flour, soda, salt, cloves, ginger and cinnamon; add to first mixture.
Chill.
Roll in one-inch balls; roll in sugar and place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour and cocoa in bowl.
Mix milk and egg yolks in pan and heat.
Add dry ingredients and cook until thickened. Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites and pour over pie and brown.

title: dirt cake
directions: Prepare cake and pudding as directed.
When cake is cool, crumble in plastic cups; layer pudding, Cool Whip and cake on top. Put worms on top of cake to look like they are crawling out of the "Dirt".

title: butter goo bars
directions: 1st Layer: Mix cake mix, margarine and egg.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: fleish kueckla
directions: Beat eggs; add salt and milk.
Mix soda and baking powder with milk mixture and egg mix.
Add flour and mix well.
Let sand an hour.
Roll thin into circles.
Fill with hamburger mix.
Seal edges with water drops.
Deep fat fry!
Good luck!

title: pork spareribs
directions: Cut each rib separately; wash and drain.
Lay in large baking dish, lined with foil.
Salt and pepper.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil and bake 30 minutes or until browned.

title: chicken gumbo(louisiana style)
directions: Cook chicken in 2 tablespoons oil until it changes color, then add celery, garlic, bell pepper and flour.
Stir for 5 minutes. Then add salt, pepper, water and red pepper.
In skillet fry okra, without flour or meal.
Then drain on paper towels when done. Just 1/2 hour before everything is done add okra and tomato.
May add more salt and water if needed.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger in pan.
At same time, boil water to cook noodles for 10 minutes.
Drain hamburger.
Add marinara sauce. Simmer until ready to put together lasagne.
Grate cheeses.
Drain noodles.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, layer 4 noodles on the bottom. Pour 1/3 sauce over noodles.
Cover with 1/3 cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 375° oven.
Cool for 5 minutes. Cut and serve.

title: oven chow mein
directions: Brown meats until no longer pink, stirring well to break up. Combine other ingredients in a 2-quart casserole with the meat. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Stir once or twice while baking.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: You will need gallon size Ziploc bags.

title: buttermilk nut candy
directions: Combine and cook sugar, salt, baking soda and buttermilk until a soft ball forms in cold water.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Beat until mixture is thick and creamy; drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let stand until cool and set.

title: sauerkraut and kielbasa
directions: Boil sauerkraut; don't drain can.
Bring to boil only, then drain.
Rinse with warm water 3 or 4 times.
Saute onion in large frying pan with oil until soft.
Add brown sugar, ketchup, salt and pepper, then add sauerkraut.
Let stew 10 minutes, then add kielbasa (don't boil kielbasa first).
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: dutch funnel cakes
directions: Beat milk and eggs together.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Pour through a funnel and fry until brown at 375°.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish, 12 x 7 x 2-inch.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; set aside.
Combine water, oil, margarine and cocoa in a saucepan and bring to a rapid boil.
Remove from heat, stir well and pur into flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes in a well-greased cake pan.

title: fried chicken
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on chicken. Coat chicken with flour. Dip in buttermilk and then coat in flour again. Heat oil. Add chicken, 4 or 5 pieces at a time.
Fry until brown on one side. Turn and brown on other side.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot.

title: freezer peaches
directions: Bring water and sugar to a good boil.
Add peach jello.
Cool. Slice peaches in containers and pour syrup over them.
Freeze.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, eggs, flavoring and nutmeg.
Scald milk and slowly add to mixture, stirring as you pour.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes, depending on your oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Crumble bacon.
Mix softened cream cheese, Miracle Whip, Parmesan cheese and 3 or 4 pieces of bacon.
Shape into a ball. Sprinkle the rest of the bacon over cheese ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: mild ginger cookies
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar.
Then
add remaining ingredients. Roll in
balls and dip in sugar.
Bake
on
ungreased
cookie sheet at 350° for 12 minutes.
Yields approximately 3 dozen.

title: torones(banana fritters)
directions: Peel ripe bananas.
Cut lengthwise into 2 parts.
Dip each part in brown sugar.
Wrap with lumpia wrapper, folding ends well.
Deep fry.
Makes 20 torones.

title: sauerkraut and ribs
directions: Stew ribs with hot pepper and cut up onion.
Midway through cooking process, add homemade sauerkraut and cook for 20 minutes.

title: melt-in-your mouth biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients until smooth and blended well.
Spoon into muffin tins (fill each cup about 3/4 full). Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
If usually large muffin tins, you may have to bake them about 15 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Mix soup, mushrooms and juice, mayonnaise, bell pepper, pimiento and onion thoroughly.
Pour over drained macaroni; mix well.
Grate cheese and stir into macaroni mixture.
Place in a baking dish.
Melt butter; mix with 1/2 box Town House crackers (crushed).
Cover top of casserole and bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening in a bowl, mixing well.
Add sugar, one cup at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla, mix well. Pour into tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake in cold oven at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Do not open oven.

title: peanut butter crispy cookies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup completely and bring to a good boil.
Boil for only 30 seconds.
Add peanut butter.
Mix this fast and add vanilla flavoring.
Pour this mixture over 4 cups of corn flakes. You can add pecans or walnuts if you like.
Quickly take 2 spoons and shape into cookies (any size, but most people like 2-inch cookies).
Bake in 325° oven until brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix the sugar, corn syrup and water in a greased 2-quart saucepan.
(I use Pam cooking spray.)
Stir constantly and cook the mixture to 238° on a candy thermometer or the soft ball stage. Add the margarine and the peanuts.
Still stirring, cook the mixture to 300° or the hard crack stage.
Remove the pan from the burner and add the vanilla and soda.
Stir until the mixture becomes foamy.
Spread the mixture on a greased cookie sheet.
Let it cool, then break it into bite-size pieces.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; form dough into 1 1/2 inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. With a fork that has been dipped in flour, gently press crisscross pattern in dough balls. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: champagne salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with sugar.
Mix pineapple, strawberries, bananas and Cool Whip together.
Add to cream cheese and sugar.
Freeze.
Makes enough for 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: teriyaki(cooking on the outdoor grill)
directions: Sprinkle tenderizer on each side of meat (if desired).
Pierce deeply with fork; leave at room temperature for 1 hour.
Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Marinate in mixture of remaining ingredients.
Brush with marinade as they are grilled on gas or charcoal grill.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together.
Let sherbet melt a little before serving.

title: artichoke chicken
directions: In a shallow dish, combine the flour, salt and pepper; mix well. Dip the chicken in the flour mixture, coating completely. Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and saut for 3 to 4 minutes per side or until golden. Add the wine, sun-dried tomatoes and artichokes. Squeeze the lemon over the chicken and cook for 2 to 4 minutes or until the sauce begins to glaze and no pink remains in the chicken.

title: broccoli company casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add broccoli, rice, soup and half a pound of Velveeta, cut into cubes.
Stir until the cheese is melted.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with remaining Velveeta, sliced, and continue baking until cheese begins to melt.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Cut cheeses into squares.
Lightly grease or Pam a 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Divide macaroni into 2 parts.
Layer half the macaroni in casserole.
Sprinkle half of both cheeses over macaroni layer.
Dust with flour (approximately 1/4 to 1/2 cup).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Layer remaining macaroni on top of first layer.
Add remaining cheeses.
Dust with flour again and salt and pepper.
Cover with milk.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until brown and crusty on top.

title: lemonade
directions: Cut lemons; squeeze lemons in 1/2 water.
Pull inside of lemons into water.

title: knorr spinach dip
directions: Thaw frozen spinach and squeeze dry.
Stir 1 package of vegetable soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until blended. Stir in spinach and chopped green onions.
Cover and chill.
Cut out center of Hawaiian bread and fill with dip.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix dressing, onions and cream cheese together and spread onto tortilla all over leaving about an inch from edge.
Finely chop pimentos and jalapenos after draining.
Sprinkle on top of cream cheese mixture, then roll tortilla.
Chill for 12 hours in refrigerator.
Cut ends off rolls and discard.
Cut rolls into 1-inch slices.
Arrange on platter.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add seasoning, V-8 juice and chili beans.
Simmer for about 1 hour.

title: master meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and pack lightly into meat loaf pan. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Glaze meat loaf with a mixture of ketchup and mustard; return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: pepper-herb mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store, covered, in airtight container.
Shake before using to blend.
Makes 1/3 cup.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, soup mix and onion.
Chill.
Roll in bacon bits.
Serve with crackers.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, milk and soup mix; shape into casserole dish and put potatoes on top.
Add 1/2 package of onion soup mix; pour on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Dip pieces of pork in beaten egg and roll over cornstarch.
Fry in oil over medium heat until light brown.
Drain.
Quickly saute garlic in 3 tablespoons oil, then add red peppers, green peppers, green onions, pineapple and pork.
Stir well.
Sprinkle with wine; stir in Sweet and Sour Sauce and bring to a boil.
While boiling, add dissolved cornstarch and stir well until mixture is thick and clear.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Bring salt, black pepper, vinegar, oil, water and sugar to a boil; cool.
Mix all vegetables.
Stir in cooked mixture and refrigerate.
Will keep one month.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Slowly blend in vanilla and flour. Gently mix in potato chips.
Drop by well-rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet and flatten lightly with a fork.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or until barely brown on bottom. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool, if desired.

title: pronto enchiladas
directions: Cook beef in large skillet; drain. Stir in cream of chicken soup and half of Ro-Tel. Spoon 1/2 cup beef mixture down center of each tortilla. Sprinkle each with 2 1/2 tablespoons cheese. Roll up tortillas and place each, seam down, in a lightly greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Pour cheese soup over tortillas. Sprinkle remaining Ro-Tel and cheese over the soup. Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes. Uncover and bake 5 more minutes. Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl and beat.
Add water to thin, if necessary; however, the thicker the batter, the better. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
You can substitute 1 cup of chocolate chips for the raisins if you wish.

title: low country ham quiche
directions: Line 9 inch quiche or pie pan with pastry. Bake for 3 minutes at 400°. Remove from oven and prick with a fork & bake 5 minutes longer. Let cool. Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk. Mix thoroughly, stir in ham, cheese and onion. Pour into pastry bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: bagels
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, yeast and salt in a bowl.
Stir in hot water and honey; beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Stir in enough of remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured surface; continue to work in flour until dough is stiff enough to knead.
Knead until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes). Cover and let rest 15 minutes.
Divide into 12 equal parts.
Shape each into flattened ball.
With thumb and forefinger, poke hole in center.
Stretch and rotate until hole enlarges to about 1 or 2 inches (it will shrink in rising and baking).
Cover and let rise about 2 minutes on a cookie sheet.
Broil about 3 minutes about 5 inches from broiler.
Boil water in large skillet.
Water should be about 2 inches deep.
Boil a few bagels at a time for about 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Drain on towel about 5 minutes.
Place on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Brush with mixture of egg white and water.
Bake at 375° 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 large bagels, 5 to 6 inches across.

title: brandi's brownies
directions: Mix together with a spoon.
Bake at 350° in an 8 x 8-inch pan for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: okra croquettes
directions: Beat egg.
Add flour, corn meal, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Stir in okra and onion.
Drop by tablespoonful into hot oil.
Cook 3 minutes or until golden brown, turning once and flattening with spatula.
Serves 4.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Melt cheese into meat.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread on party rye bread and bake at 350° until they bubble.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix
together
the frozen orange juice, frozen lemonade and apple
cider.
Heat
on low.
Begin heating tea bags in a little water.
While
they are boiling, add red hots to fruit juice mixture
and let them melt.
After tea has steeped, add it	to the fruit juice mixture, then add 3 quarts of water to it.	If not sweet enough, add sugar to taste.

title: hot clam and cheese spread
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Add onion and bell pepper; saute over direct heat for 3 minutes.
Add clams, cheese, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, milk and cayenne.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring often.
Make a day before, if you like.
Transfer to a chafing dish.
Serve on Melba toast rounds or squares of buttered pumpernickel with thin slices of garlic pickle.
Spread on top of pickle.

title: spanish gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients in a stainless steel or glass bowl. Cover and chill at least 4 hours. Serve in chilled cups; top with croutons.

title: rosy pear compote
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cranberry sauce, sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon and ginger.
Bring to a boil.
Place pears and oranges in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour cranberry mixture over fruit. Cover and bake in 325° oven for 40 minutes or until pears are tender.
Spoon into dishes and serve warm. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter blossom
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Kisses. Shape into balls and roll each ball in sugar and place on cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°. Remove. Press Kiss into center of each cookie. Return to oven for 2 minutes. Remove and let cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla; then add strawberries, food coloring and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour mixture in pie shells.
Cover and place in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix well.
Makes 5 to 8 servings.

title: summer cider punch
directions: Cook water and sugar in saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Combine juices in a pitcher. Add cooled syrup and serve over ice cubes.
Yield:
5 cups punch.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until frothy, then add remaining ingredients. Freeze in 1 gallon ice cream freezer.
For fruit flavored ice cream, substitute 1 cup mashed sweetened fruit for 1 cup milk.

title: baked squash
directions: Wash and cut up squash.
Boil, drain and mash.
Add all ingredients to squash except 1/2 cup butter.
Pour into baking dish.
Spread with melted butter-sprinkled crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: pork chop and apple bake
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Bake in hot oven (400°) until browned.
Top with apple slices; sprinkle brown sugar over apples.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Pour 1/4 cup wine over chops.
After 10 minutes, add remaining wine.
Bake 20 minutes longer, basting occasionally with wine from dish.
Serves 6.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon in large skillet and remove grease.
Crumble bacon and add all remaining ingredients to skillet and fry until liquid is absorbed and cabbage is done.

title: fruit dip
directions: Fry onions and meat until meat is no longer pink.
Drain. Stir in remaining ingredients and cook until warmed through. Transfer to a casserole dish and garnish as desired.
We use shredded Cheddar cheese, chopped green onion and sometimes sliced black olives. Scoop up with white tortilla chips and enjoy!

title: spring salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
When it starts to gel, add mayonnaise and whip for 2 minutes.
Add celery, onions and green pepper.
Add cottage cheese.
Add cucumbers.
Set to gel.
Makes 1 ring mold.

title: sausage slop casserole
directions: Make macaroni and cheese per instructions.
Steam or fry sausage and broccoli.
Slop all together with onions and oregano. Warm and serve.

title: caesar salad
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise, water, lemon juice, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and pepper in a small bowl. Mix until creamy. Combine lettuce and dressing in a large bowl. Toss well to coat. Sprinkle with croutons.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix like biscuits.
Roll out and cut the shape you want.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: brie appetizer round
directions: Remove rind from top of cheese, cutting within 1/4 inch of outside edges.
Place cheese on ungreased baking sheet and arrange pecans over top.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: chicken barbecue bake
directions: May brown chicken.
Arrange chicken, skin side down, in 9 X 13 pan.
Simmer soup mix and dressing 10 minutes.
Spread over chicken.
Marinate one hour or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, covered.
Turn; bake 20 minutes longer, uncovered, until brown and tender.
Baste often.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Coat roast with flour and put in pot.
Mix rest together and pour over the roast.
Cook 8-10 hours on low.
Serve over noodles or potatoes.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add tomato sauce, water and bouillon. Cook 3 minutes.
Add spice, salt, garlic and hot sauce; simmer 40 minutes.
Add beans and cornmeal; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus. Keep juice.
Chip up asparagus in bottom of dish.
Pour soup over asparagus.
Drain peas.
Keep juice.
Pour peas over the asparagus.
Pour juices together.
Pour half the juice over the mixture.
Add peeled and diced eggs.
Salt and pepper to taste. Add grated cheese.
Melt 3/4 stick oleo.
Break 6 to 7 slices of bread and mix with melted oleo.
Put on top of grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 400° or until top is brown.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Sift flour and spices.
Add milk and eggs; mix well.
Bake at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash in 1/2-inch pieces, cook in salted water until soft.
Mix sour cream and cheeses in a separate bowl.
Spray a 9 x 12-inch baking dish with Pam.
Drain squash and put into dish. Top with cheese mixture.
Sprinkle on croutons and pats of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bootlegger beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Boil together sugar, butter and milk; let boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add vanilla, marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Stir until smooth and melted.
(One cup chopped nuts can be added at this point, if desired.) Pour into a lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: fresh fruit with plain yogurt* * * * *
directions: My aunt gave me my first spaghetti recipe years before I was married.
It called for ten cents worth of ground beef.
I don't know how long she had had it or how much ten cents worth was.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Combine chicken broth, soy sauce, pineapple juice, sherry and ginger.

Coat wok or large skillet with nonstick vegetable cooking spray. Heat over high heat. Brown chicken and garlic. Remove. Stir-fry peppers, celery, mushrooms and snow peas for 2 minutes. Add soy mixture and chicken.
Cook 2 minutes. Add sprouts and heat through.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package. Grease 9 x 13 baking dish. Put layer of macaroni, sliced Colby cheese, grated Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper, another layer of macaroni, Colby cheese and some Velveeta cheese. Top with grated Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper. Dot top with pats of margarine and pour milk over the macaroni until it comes almost to the top. Bake at 375° about 45 minutes. (If cheese starts getting too brown, cut temperature back to 350°.)

title: chocolate chip pudding
directions: Make pudding by directions.
Add 1/2 c. extra of milk per box to thin.
Layer pudding and cookies until all are used.
Chill overnight.

title: easy fruit pizza
directions: Pat slightly softened cookie dough into two 12-inch greased pizza pans to form crust.
Press dough around rims of pans to form standing edge. Prick with fork and bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from oven and cool.

title: jam squares
directions: Cream sweet butter with granulated sugar.
Add egg yolks and flour.
Press on large cookie sheet, which has been buttered. Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 300° oven.
Cool.
Spread with raspberry jam.

title: shirley fromm's barbecued hamburger
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Simmer, covered, until carrots are tender, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve on heated buns.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Drain beans and place in casserole.
Pour mixture of other ingredients over top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: marsha's poppy seed bread
directions: Mix
cake
mix,
pudding mix, oil and eggs.
Add water. Mix well.
Add poppy seed.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: grandmother's potato salad
directions: Cube potatoes; cook until done, but not too soft.
Drain, cool and add other ingredients.
Serves 20.

title: breakfast burrito
directions: Scramble sausage cooking till brown with grated potatoes. Drain.
Scramble eggs in another pan.
Warm tortillas divide eggs and meat mixture onto tortillas.
Salt and pepper
to taste. Divide cheese on top.
Roll and warm in microwave.
Serve with salsa if desired.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl to make stiff batter. Grease another bowl.
Put dough in and turn it over, putting oily side on top.
Cover lightly with foil; let stand overnight or all day.
Do not refrigerate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cream margarine with 2 cups sugar.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat together.
Add dry ingredients to mixture.
Chill dough.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 8 dozen.

title: rich coconut pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Sprinkle in flour and blend until smooth.
Mix in remaining ingredients and spoon into pastry shell.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and beat after each one.
Add flour and Hershey's syrup.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: gobblety gooks
directions: Mix butter, sugar, brown sugar, milk, cocoa and salt in saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute at low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, quick oats and flour to ingredients in saucepan.
Stir.
Drop on waxed paper on a tray.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: almond cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, thoroughly stir together the 3/4 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir about 1 cup hot mixture into the egg yolks.
Return the egg mixture to saucepan; bring to a gentle boil.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat and stir in butter, chopped almonds and extract.
Pour into pastry shell; cover surface with clear plastic wrap.
Chill 4 to 6 hours.
In a chilled bowl, whip cream with 1/4 cup sugar until soft peaks form.
Spoon onto pie.
Garnish with maraschino cherries and toasted slivered almonds.

title: chicken and rice pilaf
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients except chicken, butter and seasonings.
Brush chicken breasts with butter.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Cover.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) 1 hour and 15 minutes or until chicken and rice are tender.

title: joanne's homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except milk.
Pour into freezer and fill remainder of freezer with milk.
(May substitute skim milk.)

title: cookie easter baskets
directions: Using Pillsbury slice and bake sugar cookie dough, you can figure about 12 baskets from a roll.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice
and boil squash with chopped onion until tender. Drain and
place	in
a
3 or 4-quart casserole dish, layering squash with
cheese,
margarine and salt and pepper. Sprinkle crushed crackers
on top with some margarine. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until bubbling.

title: hungarian coffee cake
directions: Shape dough into walnut-sized balls.
Dip into margarine; then into mixture of sugar, cinnamon and nuts.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Slice half of the berries and add 1/2 cup sugar; set aside. Reserve 1/2 cup whole berries for garnish.
Mash the rest of the berries in saucepan. Combine cornstarch, water, lemon juice and salt. Add to mashed berries and cook until clear.
Cool. Add sliced berries and turn into pie crust. Chill until set.
Top with cream and garnish with whole strawberries.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, salt and pepper; cook and drain. Add flour and stir well.
Add undrained mushrooms and soup.
Stir well and bring to a bubbling heat.
Add sour cream and chow mein noodles.
Stir well and serve.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix the sugar, cornstarch, salt, vinegar and beet juice together and cook until sauce is clear.
Add the cooked sauce to the beets and keep in warm place for 30 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons butter.

title: peanut butter chocolate balls
directions: Combine first seven ingredients, stirring well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt paraffin in top of a double boiler; add semi-sweet morsels and heat until melted, stirring constantly. Place several peanut butter balls in chocolate mixture; roll with a spoon.
Remove and place on waxed paper to cool.
Reheat chocolate if it thickens during dipping.

title: green noodle and tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix undrained tuna and Cheddar cheese.
Drain noodles.
Add tuna and mix well.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until it bubbles.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage well and drain.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Tear bread in small pieces and sprinkle over butter. Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil vinegar and sugar together until sugar is dissolved. Cool.
Add Crisco oil and pour over vegetable mixture. Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: steak and pea pods
directions: Place steak, consomme, soy sauce, water and green onions in crock-pot.
Cook on low 5 to 7 hours.

title: venison roast
directions: In crock-pot, cook all ingredients together on low all night long.
You may need to add a dash of meat tenderizer.
Roast will be ready by noon.

title: date nut balls
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add sugar, nuts and dates.
Cook on very low heat for 10 minutes.
(Do not overcook.) Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Roll in balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a medium electric mixer bowl, combine Bisquick, milk and cheese until a soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: applesauce cupcakes
directions: Put in a large
mixer bowl flour, sugar, Crisco, applesauce, soda, cloves, salt
and
cinnamon; beat 2 minutes.
Add egg and beat 1 minute.
Add nuts, raisins and dates.
Blend by hand 1 minute.
Grease pans.
Bake
at
Cupcakes: 25 to 30 minutes (makes 14 to 16) or loaf cake (9 x 5-inch) 40 to 45 minutes.
Good with cream cheese or mocha frosting.

title: corn dogs
directions: Dry hot dogs well with paper towels.
Skewer with a small stick.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients until the consistency of medium thick pancake batter.
Dip hot dogs into batter until well covered.
(The secret is to have very dry hot dogs and batter not too thin.)
Place batter covered hot dogs in very hot oil and deep fry until dark, gold brown.
Keep in warmer until ready to serve.
Serve with dip, mustard or catsup.

title: jalapeno rolled tortilla bits
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients except the tortillas. Spread on one side of a tortilla.
Roll tightly.
Close with a toothpick and place on cookie sheet.
Chill quickly in freezer 10 to 15 minutes.
Slice into bite sized pieces.
Insert toothpick into each bit and serve with picante sauce.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Boil berries, water and sugar for 5 minutes or until berries pop.
Add Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Let set until cool.
Stir in other ingredients.
Chill until set.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Whip up and refrigerate.
Make ice cream with clean snow fall.

title: 7-layer bars
directions: Melt 1
cube
butter or oleo on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups graham cracker crumbs evenly over butter.
Distribute
the butterscotch chips, chocolate chips, nuts and coconut evenly over the
graham
cracker crumbs.
Drizzle can of milk over the top, trying to cover all.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: microwave eggs benedict
directions: Combine sauce mix and ingredients as package directs in a 2-cup glass measure.
Cook at High for 2 to 3 minutes or until sauce is thickened; stir once.
Prepare poached eggs.
While eggs are standing, cook ham.
Arrange ham in single layer on paper towel-lined paper plate.
Cook at Medium for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. To serve, place ham on muffin; top with egg, then sauce.
If necessary, reheat at Medium for 1/2 to 1 minute.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Layer tortilla chips, beef mixture and English cheese in a casserole dish.
Repeat.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: mel's spaghetti sauce
directions: In big pan, put bacon on medium-low; saut. Add vegetables and saute lightly. Add whole tomatoes with juice. Simmer on low. Add salt, pepper, granulated garlic and 1 cup tomato juice. Simmer until vegetables are soft, about 1 1/2 hours. Cook 1 pound spaghetti; drain. Add butter and pour sauce over. Add Parmesan cheese to taste.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add each ingredient gradually.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 3 layers (8 x 8-inch square pans). Frost with Brownstone Frosting.

title: greek salad
directions: This salad should be put together 5 to 10 minutes before ready to serve so it doesn't become too limp.
Have all ingredients ready ahead of time so it can just be dumped into a large salad bowl and tossed with dressing until all is coated.
This is a hit as a salad with a hot pan of lasagna!

title: coconut orange jello
directions: Combine orange and sugar and let stand 10 minutes.
Drain and add water to make 1 cup liquid.
Dissolve jello in warm water.
Add orange juice, water and orange rind.
When slightly thickened, fold in oranges and coconut.
Turn into individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: margaret's chili
directions: Cook ground beef in pot with 1 cup of water.
Then drain grease off and add the remaining ingredients.
Cook about 1 hour, until done, then simmer for a little while.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar well; and eggs, then add baking powder and cracker crumbs (which have been mixed together).
Slowly add the milk and rest of the ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: peachy picnic cake
directions: Combine 1/4 cup butter and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add 3/4 teaspoon almond extract; mix well.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Set aside 1 cup of cheese.
Brown meat, onion and garlic together.
Add tomato puree and simmer 7 to 10 minutes.
Add green chilies.

title: south georgia iced tea
directions: Boil 2-3 cups of water in small pot.
Place tea bags in water and turn off the heat.
Let tea bags steep about 15-20 minutes. Put sugar in pitcher first.
Use 3/4 cup sugar, adding 1/4 cup more sugar if you like really sweet tea.
Pour a small amount of cold water over sugar, just enough to cover sugar, then drain the tea into the pitcher. Stir well so the sugar dissolves.
Continue filling pitcher with water or ice (to chill right away) and stirring until pitcher is full.
Pour over ice in tall glass or mason jar.
This tea tastes best when using the same pot for making tea, and nothing else.

title: macaroni salad
directions: While macaroni is still hot, add oil, vinegar, onion and salt. Mix and cool; refrigerate 2 hours or overnight, then add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate and chill well before serving. Without the ham it is still good.

title: shrimp spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook first 8 ingredients about 10 minutes and add shrimp.
Cook noodles separate, then add alternately in layers spaghetti and sauce in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add cheese on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: wilma's cherry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in pastry-lined pan and dot with butter.
Put on top crust, turn under edges and seal.
Prick crust.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: parmesan cheese straws
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add cheese and butter.
Process until blended.
Add flour, salt and red pepper; process about 30 seconds or until mixture forms a ball, stopping often to scrape down sides.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine cheese, onion, celery, sour cream, corn, green beans and soup.
Mix well and put in buttered casserole dish.
Crumble crackers and spread over casserole.
Slice margarine and place on top.
Bake at 300°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on a regular size cookie sheet.
Press seams together.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool thoroughly.
Cream together cream cheese, Ranch dressing and mayonnaise.
Spread over dough.
Cut dough into 1 1/2-inch squares. Mix vegetables and cheese together.
Sprinkle over cream mixture. Refrigerate 3 hours.
Before serving, heat under broiler long enough to melt cheese.

title: creole okra
directions: Saute okra, onion and green pepper in butter 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes; stirring occasionally.
Yields two servings.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cool milk and add egg, salt, sugar and flour.
Mix and knead.
Let rise until double in size. Roll out in circles and brush with melted oleo.
Cut in pie shape wedges; roll up.
Brush with oleo again.
Let rise.
Bake 15 minutes in 400° oven or until golden brown.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix second 3 ingredients and spread on top.
Bake in oven at 350° until set and brown.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Mix all ingredients in frying pan with ground beef.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole(no salt needed)
directions: Wrap each piece of chicken in bacon.
Cover bottom of flat greased baking dish with chipped beef.
Arrange breasts on chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: hamburger soup  - mexican
directions: Brown hamburger and some onion.
Drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Spread rice over bottom of 10 x 13-inch cake pan.
Lightly salt.
Add all four cans of soup.
Place onion, mushrooms and bell pepper over the top.
Slice margarine and dot over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Shape in loaf and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: german potato salad
