directions: Fry bacon; drain.
Saute onion in fat until golden brown. Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in water and vinegar.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in potatoes and the crumbled bacon.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream butter, cheese and sugar, then add other ingredients and beat 5 minutes.
Place in a lightly greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line muffin pans with paper baking cups.
Make cake mix according to package directions.
Spoon batter into muffin pan, filling each cup 2/3 full.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg. Stir in chips.
Drop 1 teaspoon of cheese mixture into each cup cake.
Bake as cake mix package directs.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese until smooth; add taco seasoning.
Place mixture in bottom of pie pan.
Top with tomatoes, lettuce and then both cheeses.
Before serving, pour taco sauce over cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips, crackers, etc.
(Keep refrigerated until serving; can be made night before.)

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in buttermilk and set aside.

Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly. Make a well in center of mixture; add reserved yeast mixture and stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 3 or
4 times. Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are lightly browned. Yield:
3 1/2 dozen.

title: yam and apple casserole
directions: Drain yams (save 1 cup of syrup); slice yams.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Butter a large casserole (about 4 quart size) and arrange apples and yams in layers.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel.
Crumble and set aside.
In bacon drippings, saute onion until tender.
Remove from heat.
Combine flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Stir into onion mixture.
Add water and vinegar.
Return to heat; cook, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute. Place potatoes and bacon in a large bowl.
Pour sauce over and toss gently.
Serve warm.

title: simplified egg casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cut or tear bread into 1-inch pieces (forget the butter).
Mix bread and cheese; pour over mixture of beaten eggs, milk and salt.
May dot with butter (not necessary).
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 50 minutes or more, so it won't be soggy in the center.
Easy and great.

title: disappearing marshmallow bars
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and butter over medium heat and cool. Add flour,	brown
sugar, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla, then add mini marshmallows, chocolate chips and nuts. Spread in a 9 x
13-inch
pan.	Bake
at
350°	for
to 25 minutes.
The center
will
be
"jiggly"	when
bars are done. When cool, the center firms up.
Cut into bars.

title: milk custard
directions: Heat milk just to boiling in small saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Mix eggs and flour in small bowl.
Stir about 1/4 cup hot milk into egg mixture.
Stir egg mixture into milk in saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cool until warm.
Stir in nutmeg and NutraSweet Spoonful.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti.
(May need to use a little more than a small box of spaghetti.)
Brown and drain ground chuck.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add Italian seasoning and garlic powder to spaghetti sauce to taste.

Grease 11 x 13-inch dish and layer spaghetti, Parmesan cheese (light coating), ground chuck, Parmesan cheese, spaghetti sauce, Parmesan cheese and shredded Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crunchy asparagus casserole
directions: Line casserole dish with chips. Cut and layer eggs over chips. Combine juice with soup to make thin sauce. Pour over eggs and arrange asparagus over top and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. (Serves 8.)

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Add the milk to cover up to 1/2 of the chocolate.
Also add sugar.
Heat slowly until thick and smooth.
Add the rum.
Let cool to room temperature.
Beat the egg whites in a separate bowl until stiff.
Beat the whipping cream until stiff.
Fold chocolate mixture into egg whites, then fold chocolate mixture into whipping cream.
You can top with additional whipping cream and chocolate swirls, if desired.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: On July 4, 1776, the Declaration of Independence was signed.
A number of the signers were volunteer fire fighters, including: John Hancock, Ben Franklin and James Wilson.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Add 2 cups hot water to Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Set in the refrigerator. Grind up cranberries, oranges and apples. Add crushed pineapple and cup of sugar. Stir all ingredients into the Jell-O mixture. Refrigerate until set.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir in butter.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a crust in buttered casserole dish.
Cook ground beef with onion until brown.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Heat through.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of spaghetti crust.
Fill pie with sauce mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and bake an additional 5 minutes until cheese melts.

title: cranberry cheer
directions: Put juices and salt in coffee percolator.
Put cinnamon sticks and cloves in basket of percolator.
Perk.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of 6 peppers.
Remove the seeds and fillers. Cook in
boiling water 2 or 3 minutes.
Drain and fill. Moisten with water or juice from sausage and bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: imperial crab
directions: Cook green pepper and onions until soft in butter.
Mix egg and other ingredients all together with cooked onions and peppers. Put in ramekins and top with bread crumbs and melted margarine or mayonnaise.
Bake 15 minutes at 475°.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add catsup, 3/4 cup water, lemon juice, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and pepper.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Season chicken with salt and dip in sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste with sauce several times during baking.

title: plum cake
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar; add eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to butter and sugar mixture.
Add almond extract.
Place plums, skin side down.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon mix.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: the best sugar cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar, eggs and extract.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Roll dough and cut. Bake on ungreased cool cookie sheets 5 to 8 minutes (cook very quickly).
Recipe can be tripled.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion, peppers and garlic in oil until onion is soft. Add tomatoes and seasoning to onion mixture.
Place rice in casserole dish that has been greased. Pour tomato mixture over top of rice.
Cover with cheese and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: easy vanilla homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into freezer.
Fill to fill line on freezer with regular milk.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour over asparagus in baking dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Put Veg-All into a big pot, undrained.
Cook over low heat. Add Ragu.
Brown ground beef in a separate pan.
Drain.
Add ground beef to the mixture with season salt and pepper.
Add water to desired consistency.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes over medium heat.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Sift and add flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add oatmeal.
Roll the dough into balls the size of walnuts and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 375° for about 7 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and carrots. Then add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg. Pour into well-greased tube pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Spray a large flat 9 x 13-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Put a thin layer of sliced, cooked ham (cut in small pieces) on bottom of dish.
Layer Swiss cheese on top.
Break eggs over cheese.
Prick yolks and let run.
Gently pour whipping cream around eggs.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Season top with white and black pepper.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Let set 10 minutes before serving in 6 large slices.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Stir in brown sugar and cream together.
Beat eggs and add to sugar mixture.
Add self-rising flour, vanilla, nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix and pour into large greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: hard times potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes in a large pan until done.
Drain 1/2 the juice from the potatoes.
Add the butter and stir until melted.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients, saving 1/2 the nuts.
Shape into a ball and roll in crushed nuts.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: egg yolk pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Cut in lard.
Place egg yolks in cup.
Fill with water to 3/4 full.
Add slowly to flour mixture.
Stir with a fork. Roll out as usual. This freezes well after rolling and put in pan.
Makes 3 (9-inch) crust shells.

title: cinnamon pound cake
directions: Mix
cake mix, sour cream, eggs, butter and oil in large bowl; mix
for 7 minutes.
Pour half of mixture in floured and greased tube pan.
Sprinkle half of sugar and cinnamon mixture on top of batter.
Add rest of batter and sprinkle with remaining mixture. Put in cold oven;
heat at 325°.
Bake 1 hour.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems of mushrooms and chop finely.
Combine stems, cheese, margarine and onion.
Fill caps.
Place on cookie sheet. Boil 2 to 3 minutes or until top of filling is slightly crusty. Serve hot.

title: nutmeg pear cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients. In another bowl, whisk the sugar, oil, eggs, cider and vanilla. Add to the dry ingredients and stir well. Stir in pears and pecans. Pour into greased and floured 10 inch fluted tube pan. Bake at 350° for 65 - 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt
butter
and
chocolate on low heat.
Blend.
Turn off heat.
Add milk and set aside.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, eggs,
vanilla
and chocolate mix.	Pour in pie shells. Combine coconut and pecans.
Sprinkle over pie.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cover with foil last 15 minutes.

title: deer over coals
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except the deer and mushrooms, in a large pot.
Add steaks and marinate in refrigerator 6 hours.
If the meat is frozen, do not defrost, just increase the marinating time by at least 2 hours.
Cook the steaks on a grill over hot coals for about 4 minutes on each side or until doneness, basting with marinating sauce several times.
Heat the mushrooms in butter for a steak topping.

title: big cookie cake
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° in a pizza type pan that will make thin cookie shape.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.

title: cool whip banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding and 2 cups of milk. Beat with mixer 2 minutes. Add Dime Brand milk and Cool Whip. Beat. Pour in bowl with vanilla wafers and bananas. Chill before serving.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Cook meat
until brown; drain fat.
Slice onion and mix with beans,
barbecue sauce, mustard, salt and meat.
Stir, if dry, add more
barbecue
sauce or ketchup.
Cook in oven 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Peel potatoes and mash with melted margarine.
Beat in sugar, flour and flavorings.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add milk; beat and then pour into two unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Makes two 8-inch pies.

title: stacy's muffins
directions: Stir together nonfat dry milk, brown sugar, water, oil, egg white and vanilla in medium bowl.

Combine flours, wheat germ, baking soda, baking powder and spices; stir into sugar mixture. Stir in remaining ingredients (carrots, zucchini, bananas or pumpkin plus optional fruits) except sesame seed.
Pour into 12 paper muffin cups or greased muffin pans.
Sprinkle with sesame seed. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
(Keep them moist by not overbaking.) Remove from pans.
Cool.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Cook the raisins in enough water to cover.
Beat together the cream, egg yolks, sugar and flour.
Add to raisins and cook until thick.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue made from the egg whites.

title: green cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake according to mix directions.
Mix the first 3 ingredients of frosting recipe on low speed for 1 minute. Fold in thawed Cool Whip.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Mix
ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° to 350° until golden brown.

title: vacuum cleaner cookies
directions: Combine margarine, cake mix and 1 egg.
Stir together until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pat into bottom of a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan (well-greased).
Beat remaining 2 eggs lightly, then beat in cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour over mixture in jelly roll pan, spreading evenly.

title: salmon croquettes or patties(4 or 5 servings)
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon.
Beat egg and add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Form into 2 ounce patties.
Serve with tartar sauce or creamed pea sauce.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan until golden brown.
Don't overbake.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolates in double boiler.
Add peanuts.
Drop onto waxed paper; let set.

title: hot dish
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and onions.
Layer in casserole dish. Spread corn over potatoes and onions.
Spread tomato soup over mixture and place sliced sausage patties over top.
Cover.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Remove cover and brown sausage.
Serve with salad and bread.

title: praline uniques
directions: Arrange Triscuit wafers in single layer, trimming to fit if necessary on well-greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan; set aside.
In saucepan over medium heat, melt margarine.
Remove from heat, stir in brown sugar, egg, flour and vanilla until well blended.
Pour over Triscuits, spreading to cover wafers. Sprinkle with pecan pieces.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool; cut into squares following outline of Triscuits.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: In a saucepan, mix together sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa. Cook for 1 1/2 minutes.
After it starts to boil, add oats, peanut butter, nuts and vanilla.
Drop cookie mix by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil vinegar and sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add oil and mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Can be made ahead of time and will keep for days.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pineapple.
Take can of milk with lemon juice and pecans.
Mix all together and pour into pie shells.
Let chill about 2 hours.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together the beef, eggs, bread crumbs and onion soup mix. Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish (do not brown).
Mix cranberry sauce, sauerkraut, chili sauce and brown sugar; pour over meatballs.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Slice apples and dip in lemon juice to prevent browning.
Place on a dish.
Spread cream cheese in large shallow serving dish.
Top with caramel and pecans.
Dip apples in and enjoy!

title: apple pancakes
directions: Mix until the only lumps are apple pieces. Cook on a medium heat griddle until bubbles form and break and the sides start to solidify before flipping.

title: royal flounder fillets
directions: Sprinkle fillets with salt and pepper.
Arrange in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove fillets with a slotted spatula; place on a heated ovenproof platter and keep warm.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice the onion.
Saute onion and celery in butter in 1-gallon soup kettle.
When tender, add the flour and mix to make smooth paste.
Add the chicken stock, water, carrots and potatoes, diced very fine.
Simmer for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Add the milk, curry powder, white pepper and salt to taste.
Bring to simmer again for a few minutes.
Serve hot with crisp crackers.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Mix together.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes, until set up at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil fryer until it is very well done.
Remove from broth. Cook noodles in broth, try to absorb the liquid.
Remove chicken from bones.
Now make layers.

title: punch slush
directions: Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw to a slush.
Add 7-Up.

title: elvis presley's peanut butter pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream together the peanut butter and vanilla.
Gradually add the sugar and salt, blending well.
Add the eggs and milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Turn the filling into the pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce the heat to 350° and bake for 25 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jefferson davis pie
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Beat in yolks.
Add flour, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
Stir in cream, dates, raisins and nuts.
Pour into baked shell.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes. Top with meringue when cool.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and molasses; mix well. Add dry ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in sugar and place on cookie sheet 2 1/2 to 3 inches apart.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Done when well browned and surface has cracked.

title: punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients except sherbet in a large punch bowl.
Spoon in sherbet and serve.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: barbecued hot dogs
directions: Brown onion in oil; add other ingredients (except frankfurters).
Pour over split hot dogs or sliced crosswise. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: black forest cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and pie filling by hand.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: sylvia's hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo together.
Add sugar and evaporated milk and boil 10 minutes, stirring constantly (watch that it doesn't burn).

title: wayne's flan in a pan(spanish flan; creme caramel)
directions: Melt 3/4 cup of the sugar in a heavy saucepan over moderate heat to a golden caramel, stirring constantly.
Pour caramel into a low, flat ovenproof baking dish of at least 1.5-quart capacity. Carefully tip the dish to cover the bottom with a thin, even film of the caramel.
Work quickly to spread caramel before it cools and hardens.
Set aside.

title: halloween snack mix(15 minutes or less)
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients, mix well.

title: sour cream cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and butter; press firmly on bottom of 10 to 13-inch cake pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth. Beat in eggs, then sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned around edges (center will be slightly soft).
Cool.
Chill.

title: soupy rice
directions: Combine cold water and rice in medium size pan.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Reduce heat; cover tightly.
Cook rice on low heat for 14 minutes.
(Do not lift lid during this time.)
When rice is done, add can of soup, stirring into rice, 1/4 can at a time.
Add 1/2 can "hot" water.
Cook on low heat for 3 to 5 more minutes. Serve.

title: shoga-yaki (ginger pork)
directions: Mix all ingredients except pork to make sauce.
Coat pork with sauce and let stand for 15 minutes.
Heat oil in skillet, and stir-fry meat with sauce.

title: tuna noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring until moist.
Let chill for at least an hour.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In medium saucepan, melt morsels and margarine.
Stir in crumbs and nuts. Press half the mixture firmly onto bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand, vanilla and egg.
Mix well.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onions, raisins and bacon together gently. Blend mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar thoroughly.
Fold dressing into vegetable mixture and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Mix together all ingredients but ham.
Bring to a boil; simmer 1 hour.
Add ham and simmer 1 more hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray pizza pan with Pam.
Spread cookie dough and bake as directed.
Cool and top with sugar and cream cheese mixture. Last, spread with various fruits.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Boil noodles and spray with cold water.
In a small bowl, mix sour cream and cream cheese; set aside.
Brown beef and onions; stir in tomato sauce.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Mix together and bake in covered dish at 250 degrees for 6 hours.
Can be baked at higher temperature for less time, but not as good.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash potatoes; combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shells and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
(Sprinkle nutmeg on top of pie before cooking, if desired.)
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, vanilla and butter.
Add eggs and mix.
Add oatmeal; mix.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Combine broth, onion, dill and potatoes.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Remove from heat and set aside.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Layer ingredients, starting with cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple (including juice), dry cake mix, coconut and pecans.
Drizzle melted butter over entire cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: flan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Heat sugar in small skillet over medium heat, stirring often, until syrup turns an even amber color, about 5 minutes. Divide into 6-ounce custard cups - 10 of them (about 1 teaspoon for each cup). Set cups aside.

title: pineapple-cheese mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into 1-quart mold; chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl with mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chips.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Spread evenly.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Set out until cool and ready to eat!

title: apple butter
directions: Pour applesauce into crock-pot. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook on high 8 to 10 hours. Remove cover during the last 1/2 hour of cooking. Stir occasionally.

title: mom bardo's cornbread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift together cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Then add alternately with milk. Bake in a loaf pan at 350°, about 40 minutes.
(I used cornmeal from Alderfers Pantry from Troy.)

title: crab casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Mix all ingredients and put in pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in	a bowl and put in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Top with corn flake crumbs.	Bake at 350°for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: crunchy green pea salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water (steam, if fresh); drain.
Combine vegetables, nuts and bacon with sour cream.

title: beef with tomatoes and green peppers
directions: Cut up London Broil, tomatoes, green peppers and scallions.

title: rodeo cake
directions: Flour and grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread chopped nuts over bottom.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour over nuts.
Mix softened cream cheese with sugar and margarine.
Drop by spoonfuls over cake mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza butter
directions: Mix well.
Spread on toasted English muffins or Triscuits. Broil 3 minutes.
Let pizza butter stand at room temperature before spreading.
May be frozen.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Cut in thin slices, but do not peel.
Slice onions.
Pour salt over this and let stand 2 hours.
Then drain and rinse thoroughly.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix together like pastry.
Put into pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Combine 2 cans of soup and Ro-Tel together.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place 1 tablespoon soup mixture.
Alternate layers: tortillas, chicken, onions, pepper and soup.
End with cheese. Bake at 350°, covered with foil, for 45 minutes.
Remove foil; continue baking 15 minutes longer.

title: fiesta sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all items except olives.
Wrap each olive with dough around completely.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes or until done.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Boil chicken; debone.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix soups together.
Mix stuffing according to box direction.
Grate and mix cheeses.
In casserole dish, place a layer of chicken, layer of cheese, layer of soup and layer of dressing.
Continue until all is gone.
Heat at 350° until bubbly.
Very good day after.

title: baked chicken
directions: Skin the chicken.
Dip in egg, then in Italian bread crumbs. Add 4 tablespoons butter or margarine to a pan.
Bake the chicken in a 350° oven for 40 minutes, then turn it over and bake for 20 minutes more, no cover.

title: pork chops a la jodi
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Coat chops with flour, shaking excess.
In large skillet, brown both sides in butter.
In shallow casserole dish, place chops in overlapping rows.
Spoon pan drippings over chops.
Spread soup over chops.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Preheat oven at 350° and bake, covered, for 10 minutes.
Remove cover and bake another 15 to 20 minutes. Excellent over cooked rice and peas.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: glorified chicken
directions: In skillet, cook chicken in hot oil over medium heat 10 minutes or until browned on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup and pepper.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 35 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender, stirring occasionally (approximately 45 minutes cook time).

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix everything well, adding additional mayo if not well moistened. Place in shallow baking dish and bake at 350° until hot and edges bubble. Serve on mini pumpernickel rye bread slices.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop the cabbage, green pepper and onion; mix well and refrigerate.
Mix together the sugar, salt, dried mustard, celery seed, vinegar and oil; boil until the sugar is well dissolved. Let cool and then pour over the cole slaw mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: ginny's rolled sugar cookies
directions: Blend together the shortening, sugar and eggs; add vanilla. Mix well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add half dry ingredients to wet ingredients.
Stir well; add half buttermilk, rotating with dry ingredients and buttermilk. Roll out dough on lightly floured surface.
Press cookie cutters. Decorate if desired. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Add eggs one at a time, beating after each one.
Bake at 350° in loaf pan or angel food pan.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix uncooked rice with soups.
Pour in a baking dish and layer onions and mushrooms on top.
Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Cover with tin foil and bake in a 350° oven until chicken is done, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine scooped out potato, Cheddar cheese, milk, egg, butter, salt and pepper.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Spoon an equal amount of potato mixture into each shell.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Arrange on baking sheet.
Microwave at High for 5 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in casserole dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir one time after 30 minutes.
Easy and delicious.

title: texas fudge cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and 5 tbsp. butter. Press into large cake pan. Chill for 2 hours. Mix sugar, vanilla, eggs or cream cheese and oleo. Beat for 5 minutes. Place on top of crust, chill 1 hour. Layer banana slices and pineapple. Spread Cool Whip over pineapple. Decorate with cherries, pecans and drizzle with chocolate syrup. Refrigerate. Best if sets for a few hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice and put
in
a
greased casserole.
Mix soups and sour cream together and
stir
in
chicken.
Put on top of rice. Crush about 20 Ritz
crackers and mix with melted oleo. Put on top of chicken.
Sprinkle poppy seed over this.
Put in oven and bake at 350° until bubbly hot.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine melted margarine, flour, potato flakes, milk, oregano and Parmesan.
Stir until it forms a ball.
Knead a few times to smooth out the dough.
Divide in half.
Press half into bottom and up sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not leave any holes for filling to leak through.

title: brunswick stew
directions: In a 5-gallon pot, put all meat and onions together.
Cook about 6 hours or until meat separates from bone.
Remove bones from pot and add lima beans and tomatoes.
Cook potatoes separately and mash.
Add potatoes and corn to stew about an hour before serving, then season with salt, pepper, sugar, catsup, tomato paste and butter.
Be sure to stir frequently, especially toward the last part of cooking.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and drain. Add spices. Brown onions in butter with flour. Add mixture to beef. Add soup/water (3/4 can). Simmer about 30 minutes. Remove from heat and add sour cream. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: carrot jam
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepot.
Bring slowly to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, stirring constantly until thick. Pour hot into jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Adjust caps. Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yields about 3 half pints.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Combine shortening and sugar.
Mix well.
Add molasses and egg.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to shortening mixture.
Make into balls the size of a walnut.
Dip in sugar and bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: red rice
directions: Cook rice in boiling salted water.
Cook onions, tomato sauce, tomato paste, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and pepper sauce for 10 minutes on low heat.
Mix with rice.
Place in casserole.
Cook bacon until crisp; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until rice absorbs all liquid.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix cocoa, milk and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, stir in butter and vanilla.
Serve hot or cold over ice cream.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 cups.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: All ingredients can be doubled to make more.

title: chili con carne
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add meat to brown, stirring to break up.
Drain meat.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, oregano, salt, pepper sauce and bay leaf. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring frequently. Stir in kidney beans and cook 15 minutes.
Discard bay leaf. Makes 4 servings.

title: "crunch cake"
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and beat 12 minutes with electric mixer. Bake at 275° for 1 hour or 1 1/2 hours for a much lighter and much prettier cake.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Empty cans of French onion soup and mushroom gravy into crock-pot on low setting.
Cut meat in cubes and place in crock-pot with 1/4 cup of whiskey and let simmer until meat changes color.
Add potatoes, carrots, onion and 1 cup of water. Let simmer 1 hour on low setting.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream oleo, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs to creamed mixture and stir.
Add flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt to mixture. Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Shape dough into round balls.
Roll balls into sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Immediately remove from cookie sheets!

title: potato casserole
directions: Let potatoes thaw.
Season lightly with salt and pepper and spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix next five ingredients and spread over potatoes.
Mix last two ingredients and spread on top of cheese mixture.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill at least 8 hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs and combine with sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla. Slowly add milk; mix well and pour in 9-inch pastry lined pie pan. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for about 25 minutes more or until mixture doesn't adhere to knife.

title: tortellini tapa with spicy dip
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions; drain and cool. Whisk together 1 cup dressing and eggs. Add tortellini and let stand 10 minutes. Drain and dredge in breadcrumbs. Place on a baking sheet. Chill 1 hour. Stir together remaining dressing, salsa and cilantro; chill. Pour oil into a Dutch oven; heat to 375°. Fry tortellini in batches until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Serve with dip; garnish, if desired.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Make 2 layer chocolate cake according to box directions, then cut into pieces.
Make instant chocolate pudding according to directions on box.
In glass bowl, layer chocolate cake, chocolate pudding, brickles and Cool Whip.
Layer again.
End with Cool Whip and sprinkle with brickles for decoration.
Easy to make! Delicious!!

title: rich rolls
directions: Heat milk until it's warm to the touch.
Pour over sugar in a large bowl.
Add dry yeast.
Stir in 3 cups plain flour.
Mix well. Cover and let rise, about 1 hour, until bubbly.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine jello with water.
Add juice from orange sections plus enough cold water to make 3/4 cup.
When jello is slightly set, add sherbet and orange sections.
Pour into mold which has been rinsed with cold water.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: spice cake
directions: *If self-rising flour is used, omit baking powder and salt.

title: old-fashion bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour 1/2-inch water in baking pan and place casserole in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Dribble 2 tablespoons honey on top.
Serve warm.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Blend flour, salt, mustard and pepper into 4 tablespoons melted butter; slowly stir in milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.

Add cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce and heat until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally. Combine with macaroni and spoon into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Combine bread crumbs with remaining butter and sprinkle over macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and top is golden.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pecan log
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Roll into a log shape and wrap in wax paper.
Chill before serving.
Slice off what you need.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: luscious lemon bars
directions: For crust:
Combine the 2 1/2 cup flour and sugar.
Using a pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Press into bottom of greased 15 x 10 x 1 pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes until golden.

title: morgan's little pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Layer ketchup, meat and cheese on slices of bread and cook until cheese melts.

title: marinated chilled potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain and slice, if necessary. Combine other ingredients and whisk well.
Pour over warm potatoes and toss gently.
Refrigerate.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients until it resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk and stir until it forms ball around fork. Knead 14 times, pat on floured board or waxed paper until 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and place in 2 greased 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potluck chicken
directions: Put broccoli in pan.
Add Swiss cheese, boiled ham and chicken pieces.
Cover with undiluted soup.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: wassail
directions: Mix together all ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Can be heated in party perk coffeepot, placing the spices in basket.
Can be reheated; keeps well in refrigerator for several days. Delicious on a cold day!
(Makes almost 2 gallons.)

title: family favorite peach pie
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften and mix with milk, beating until fluffy.
Spread over crust.
Lightly brush peaches with small amount of lemon juice.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Place peach slices on cream cheese layer and cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Let stand for 24 hours, then serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend all ingredients with mixer.
Chill and serve with chips or crackers.

title: sweet potato rolls
directions: Line
a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with heavy-duty aluminum foil. Dissolve
yeast
in warm water; set aside.	Scald milk. Add sugar,
salt,
spices
and	butter.
Stir until butter is almost melted.
Pour
over
sweet	potatoes;
beat
well with mixer. Stir
in
dissolved
yeast and egg.
Add 2 cups flour. Beat
well. Stir
in
enough
additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic,	8
to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in size, about 1 hour.

title: walnut meringue pie
directions: Beat egg whites with baking powder; add sugar, vanilla, crackers and nuts.
Put into 9-inch buttered pie plate.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve with cream (optional).

title: congealed ambrosia salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Chill until mixture starts to thicken.
Fold in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.

title: shake & bake mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in airtight container until needed.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Then mix pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip, then add cream cheese mixture. Make layers with mixture, then cookies; repeat.
Add gummy worms (optional).
Refrigerate.

title: noodles
directions: Stir sufficient flour into slightly beaten egg to make very stiff dough.
Add salt.
Knead and roll as thin as possible.
Cover with a towel and let remain untouched for half an hour.
Then cut in small strips and dry.
When needed, place in boiling water for 15 minutes.

title: crunchy cheese rounds
directions: Blend cheese and margarine in large bowl.
Sift flour, sugar, cayenne pepper and salt into mixture; add remaining ingredients. Work dough with pastry blender or hands.
Pinch dough into small balls 1-inch in diameter.
Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet and press down with palm of hand or fork, into small circle.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack and store in sealed container.
Handle gently.
These are very crisp.
Yield: 11 dozen.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Pour over block of ice. Just before serving, add chilled ginger ale.

title: denver biscuits
directions: Pour milk in large bowl with lard or margarine, potatoes and sugar.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add dissolved yeast, then add enough flour to make consistency of biscuit dough.
Set aside one hour. At this point, dough can be stored in refrigerator for several days.
Pinch out biscuits when wanted.
When taken from refrigerator, need to let rise for 45 minutes to 1 hour; bake at 350°.

title: one bowl holiday fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in large bowl on High, 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.

title: never fail custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla in bowl.
Heat 3 cups milk in a large saucepan and here is the secret of success or failure.
Let the milk come right up side of pan.
Watch it very close as it may cook over pan, then add hot milk slowly to ingredients and pour in unbaked crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle top of pie with nutmeg before baking if desired.

title: mound cake
directions: Make
cake according to directions on box.
Melt sugar, milk and
marshmallows
in heavy saucepan.
Simmer 3 minutes. Add coconut to mix.
Pour over cake.

title: cherry watermelon pickles
directions: Peel and slice 1/2 watermelon; wash and peel.
Soak in 2 quarts water with 2 tablespoons salt.
Let stand overnight. Drain; add clean water.
Boil 30 minutes.
Make syrup; add cherries and juice and boil 45 minutes.
Let stand in syrup overnight; heat and seal.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin and dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add eggs and milk.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: summer salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Just before serving, toss with Dressing.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: chocolate popcorn
directions: Cook until hard ball stage when dropped in cold water.
Pour over 6 quarts popcorn.
Stir until each kernel is coated with chocolate.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except the chocolate and shape into small balls.
Chill about 1 hour.
Melt several blocks of the almond bark over double boiler.
Take a toothpick, prick into the ball and dip, coating with the chocolate.
Place on wax paper. Cool and store in covered container.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except ribs.
Cook on low-medium heat until glossy.
Pour sauce over ribs and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: super cornbread
directions: Combine soup, eggs and milk.
Stir in muffin mix until blended.
Fold in sausage.
Place in greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: haupia(coconut pudding)
directions: Combine coconut milk and sugar in saucepan.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Add to coconut milk and sugar in pan; stir until smooth.
Stir over medium heat until thick.
Pour into pan. Refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook hen in plenty of broth.
Remove and cut in bite-size pieces.
Strain broth and remove most of fat.
Cook noodles in broth.
Let most of broth cook out.
Then add chicken, vegetables, soup and lemon juice.
Put in a large baking dish or roaster and cook for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
During the last 20 minutes, add cheese.
Serves 15.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles as directed on package; drain.
Brown beef; drain.
Add corn to beef mixture.
Add catsup.
Mix well.
Put in ovenproof casserole.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Continue to bake until cheese melts.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine syrup and sugar in 1 1/2-quart round microwave bowl. Stir well until evenly blended.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes. Stir in nuts; microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes, until light brown.
Stir in margarine and vanilla; blend well.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda; stir until light and foamy.
Quickly pour into lightly greased baking sheet.
Cool; break into small pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 pound.

title: tomato aspic(serves 8)
directions: Place
stewed
tomatoes
in
blender
and
blend
well. Dissolve
jello
in
hot
water
and mix with stewed tomatoes. Chopped stuffed olives
or chopped celery may be added to this mixture.
Place in square pan or Pyrex and place in refrigerator until it congeals.
Cut in blocks and serve on lettuce.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix whipping cream until thick.
Add lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk; mix well.
Mix all fruit and marshmallows together. Pour filling over this and mix.
Chill overnight.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour together.
Add milk, coconut, vanilla and oleo.
Bake at 350C for 30 - 35 minutes.
Makes its own crust.
Makes 2 pies.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix in blender at low speed for 3 minutes.
Be sure it is blended well.
Pour into a greased 9-inch glass pie pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until a knife comes out clean when inserted near the center.

title: broken glass jello
directions: Prepare 3 flavors of jello separately, using 1 cup of boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each.
Pour each flavor into an 8 or 9-inch square pan or 7 x 11-inch rectangle.
Chill overnight.

title: herbed oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a plastic or paper bag; shake to mix.
Place 2 to 3 chicken pieces in bag; shake well and set aside. Repeat with remaining chicken.

title: ambrosia
directions: Empty jello into a bowl, add 1/3 c. boiling water.
Mix well. Add about 1/4 cup pineapple juice (drained from chunks) and add about 2 cups ice cubes.
Let thicken and remove cubes.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Add all fruit, making sure it has been drained.
DO NOT add any more fruit juice.
Add about 3/4 can coconut and 1/4 bag of marshmallows.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Make a few hours in advance of serving.

title: apple casserole
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: taco rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese, chilies, onion and seasoning thoroughly. Spread over tortillas.
Roll tortillas and chill at least 12 hours.
Cut into 1-inch slices and serve with taco sauce, hot cheese dip or salsa.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries (save juice).
Drain all juice from pineapple and add to cranberry juice.
Add enough water to make 2 cups to dissolve jello in.
(Heat liquid, dissolve jello, then cool jello liquid in fridge before adding to relish.)
Mix all together and keep in fridge.
Do not freeze.
Will keep for about a month.

title: beef log
directions: Soften cream cheese until workable.
Finely chop beef, mushrooms, green onions and olives.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Form into shape desired and roll in pecans.
Chill.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: marinating sauce for meat
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour over roast and marinate at least 6 hours, turning after 3 hours.
This is excellent for beef or pork.
Charcoal broil roast (chuck takes approximately 30 minutes per side).

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread.
Put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown sausage and drain well.
Spoon over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese. Beat milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Cover raisins with water, add cloves and simmer ten minutes. Add sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper which have already been mixed together.
Stir until slightly thickened and add remaining ingredients.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter in glass bowl.
Put in all ingredients but peanut butter.
Microwave for 2 minutes and 20 seconds, then add peanut butter; stir well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan; cool in fridge.

title: fresh "apple harvest" cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to mixture.
Blend well.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Pour batter into greased and floured 12 cup fluted tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely on rack.

title: pride of iowa cookies
directions: Beat eggs, sugars and shortening.
Add nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder in a separate bowl.
Add to creamed mixture a little at a time.
Add oatmeal and mix well.
Shape into walnut size balls, press down on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 9 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Salt hamburger and fry with onions.
Melt cheese, then add everything together in a crock-pot.

title: rutabaga au gratin
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Add water to cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 12 to 15 minutes.
Melt butter in saucepan, add flour and milk until thickened and bubbly.
Add salt, pepper and cheese until it melts.
Stir in drained turnips and put in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: simple simon candy
directions: Melt chips over hot water, not boiling. Stir in peanuts; drop on waxed paper and refrigerate until firm.

title: surprise meringue kisses
directions: Beat egg whites with vanilla, cream of tartar, extract and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar about 1 teaspoon at a time.
Beat until big stiff peaks form.
Drop with a tablespoon 1 1/2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Press a chocolate kiss into each cookie.
With a knife or narrow spatula, bring meringue up and over candy.
Swirl top.
Sprinkle with green sugar.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes or until set. Immediately remove cookies to a rack.
Cool.
Makes 44.

title: cheese hash browns
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until brown around the edges.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix well with a spoon or whisk.
Pour into a graham cracker pie crust.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in small saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Roll each biscuit into a 9-inch rope.
Pinch each end to seal.
Dip circles into melted butter and then in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Twist each biscuit to form a figure 8.
Place biscuits on a baking sheet and sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: russian lasagna
directions: Cut cabbage coarsely.
Cover with water and boil for 10 minutes; drain.
Boil rice until soft but firm.
Drain.
Mix meats, eggs, seasonings, onion and 1/2 can of soup.
Add rice and mix well.
Put half of cabbage in large lasagna pan.
Spread meat mixture evenly over cabbage.
Cover with the rest of the cabbage. Dilute the half can of soup with equal amount of water.
Pour over cabbage.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: grilled turnovers
directions: Mix pie crust sticks, dry milk and water until dough loses stickiness and cleans bowl.
Remove label from unopened can of pie filling.
Lightly flour side of can.
Divide dough into 6 equal parts; roll each part on aluminum foil into 6-inch circle, using floured can as rolling pin.

title: basic risotto
directions: Warm the stock.
Have a ladle nearby.
In a heavy, wide skillet, heat the butter over medium-high heat until bubbly.
Add onion.
Saute until light gold.
Add rice, stirring and tossing the grains until well-coated, about 5 minutes.

title: mother's egg pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into 9-inch deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, lower temperature to 350° and bake 25 minutes longer.
Do not overbake.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine the cream cheese, sugar and milk with peanut butter. Mix until creamy.
Fold in whipped cream and beat lightly until mixed.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate.

title: tuna melt
directions: Mix tuna and mayonnaise in small ovenproof bowl.
Top with cheese.
Broil on high for 3 minutes.
Use on sliced bread.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is done.
Serves a lot.

title: artichoke cheese and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart saucepan, combine rice, seasoning packet, water and margarine.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low; cover and simmer until water is absorbed. Spread cooked rice in bottom of an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with half of the cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over cheese.
Top with tomato and artichokes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat sauerkraut, sugar and oil until hot through and through. Add onion, celery and bell pepper.
Heat all together.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.

title: easy cucumber relish
directions: Drain cucumbers, onions and pepper thoroughly.
Add salt. Place in a large saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 20 minutes.
Pack in jars; seal.
Yields 10 to 12 pints.

title: ham and macaroni salad
directions: Cool macaroni, rinsing starch away.
Mix lightly with other ingredients.
Chill and serve on crisp lettuce leaves.
(Cubed Cheddar cheese is a good addition to this dish.
Chopped pimento adds color to this dish.)
This is a good make-ahead dish.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 Tbsp. milk over low heat, stirring until melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese; add remaining milk and chocolate mixture, beat until smooth.
Fold 8
oz. of the Cool Whip into the chocolate mixture and blend until smooth.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Top with remaining 4 oz. of cool whip.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a small bowl, mix flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture to creamed egg mixture.
Stir in oats, chips and nuts. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls and place on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: calico vegetable salad
directions: Cook frozen vegetables until tender; cool and drain.
Combine with celery, onion and kidney beans.
Mix together the sugar, mustard, vinegar and salt; cook until clear, then cool.
Pour over the vegetables and mix.
Store in refrigerator for 3 days, stirring each day.
Delicious as a buffet vegetable or salad.

title: broiled ginger scallops
directions: If scallops are large, cut into halves.
Arrange scallops in single layer in square 8 x 8 x2-inch baking dish.
Heat soy sauce to boiling.
Add ginger root; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over scallops. Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally, for 2 hours.

title: taco lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large saucepan, cook ground beef until brown and drain well.
Add taco seasoning, garlic, cayenne pepper and water.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Set aside. Sprinkle cornmeal in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Place 6 tortilla shells in bottom of pan, overlapping and extending up sides.

title: sour cream chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix butter with the 1 cup sugar until blended, then beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir flour with baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon, then blend with creamed mixture.
Mix in sour cream.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan.
In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs with milk and butter.
Add dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Bake in prepared pan 20 minutes.

title: lemon delight
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Press in bottom of baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together except 2 slices bacon.
Lay them across the top.
Bake 3 to 4 hours at 375°.

title: tuna and peas
directions: In saucepan saute onion in butter.
Add mushroom soup, milk and peas.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Serve over toast or biscuits.

title: homemade granola
directions: In a large bowl, combine rolled oats, shredded coconut, almonds, sesame seed, sunflower seeds and wheat germ.
Combine honey and oil.
Stir into oat mixture.
Spread on a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° until golden brown, 45 to 50 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; stir in dried apricots and raisins.
Remove to another pan to cool, stirring to prevent lumping.

title: southwestern grilled chicken salad
directions: Place lettuce and hot chicken in large serving bowl.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Serve with salsa or Kraft Free ranch fat free dressing, if desired.

title: cornmeal nips
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix cornmeal, sugar, salt, onion, butter and Tabasco sauce.
Add boiling water.
Stir until absorbed.
Stir in egg.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes; remove and cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes; slice them.
Rinse before starting.
Cook potatoes until tender.
Crumble ground beef in medium saucepan. Add onion; cook until brown and onion is soft.
Use a stick of butter to grease casserole dish.
Drain grease from beef.
Place a layer of potatoes, then sliced cheese and put over potatoes.
Add layer of ground beef and onion.
Continue to do this until all potatoes, ground beef and onion are used.
Garnish with pepperoni and bacon bits, if desired.
Place in a 400° oven for 20 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Makes about 7 (1-cup) servings.

title: deviled hamburgers
directions: Combine chili sauce, mustard, onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Mix with ground beef.
Toast bread on one side under broiler.
Spread mixture on untoasted side.
Place under broiler for 6 to 8 minutes.
Serve as an appetizer or main coarse.

title: seasoned french-fried potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes (optional).
Cut into desired wedge size.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Sprinkle liberally with seasoning salt.
In a deep frying pan, heat enough oil to cover potatoes. Fry until golden brown.

title: tea punch(1 gallon)
directions: Make tea.
Mix in all ingredients, except ginger ale. Refrigerate.
Add ginger ale right before serving.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine ingredients.
If desired, top with grated cheese and chopped ham.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, except soda and popcorn, in 1 1/2-quart dish.
Bring to a boil.
Cook on high for 2 minutes in microwave.
Remove from microwave and stir in soda.
Put popcorn in large grocery sack.
Pour syrup over corn, close bag and shake. Cook in bag on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake again.
Cook another 1 1/2 minutes (may need another shake and 1 1/2 minutes). Pour in pan and allow to cool.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Stir until melted. Remove from heat.
Stir in milk, butter and vanilla.
Blend until butter is mixed with chocolate.
Stir in nuts.
Spread into an 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover for 30 minutes or until tender; drain.
Let cool to touch.
Peel and cut into 1/4-inch strips; set aside.
Combine 1/4 cup of butter, onion, salt, pepper, sour cream and soup in a large bowl; gently stir in potatoes and cheese.
Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: 5 thing salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
A few nuts may be added. Serve chilled.

title: mayonnaise(16 ounces)
directions: Blend all ingredients, except oil, at high speed for 20 seconds.
Slowly add oil, continuing to blend for about 2 1/2 minutes or until well mixed and thickened.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda.
Add vinegar, vanilla, shortening and cold water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Use 2 teaspoons per cup.

title: oriental beef stew
directions: Brown meat and onion in oil.
Drain.
Add water, soup, brown sugar, soy sauce and vinegar.
Cover.
Simmer 45 minutes or until meat is tender; stir occasionally.
Add vegetables; cover and cook 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
If thickened gravy is desired, thicken with 1 tablespoon flour, mixed with 1/4 cup water.
Serve over rice in bowls.
Lamb, pork or beef may be used.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jello fruit dessert
directions: Step 1:
Mix first 3 ingredients together and press into 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Put in freezer.

title: broccoli soup appetizer
directions: In a large saucepan, cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Add soup, milk, wine, butter, tarragon and pepper.
Heat through.
Serves 8.

title: fast and easy taco burgers
directions: Brown the meat in a skillet until it is all browned.
Drain off any grease and replace on the stove.
Add the seasoning slowly, mixing in well.
I usually use 1 1/2 packets of seasoning, but you may wish to add both or only one, depending on your taste.

title: cheesy potatoes i
directions: Melt margarine, Velveeta and half and half together in saucepan.
Pour over frozen hash browns in casserole dish. (Grease casserole dish or spray with Pam.)
Let sit for 1 hour. Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 to 60 minutes.
Let sit for about 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Potatoes will seem very liquidy when removing from oven, but will thicken up as they sit for the 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chili dogs
directions: First turn on oven to 400°.
Get pizza pan out of cabinet & take a clean dish towel & wipe pan good.
Go to the freezer and get out a big Tombstone pizza.
Take out of wrapper & put on pan. You may add more mushrooms, pepperoni & sausage if desired.
Put in oven and bake until done.

title: incident at vermicelli
directions: In a large saucepan heat the oil over medium heat.
Add the garlic and saute for 2 minutes.
Add the onions and cook for 3 minutes.
Add the onions and stir in the pepper strips and cook for 5 minutes.
Add the cream and tomato paste and season with parsley, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper.
Cook until the sauce thickens, about 10 minutes.
Add the chicken and cook until heated through. Toss the vermicelli with the chicken mixture.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Add 2/3 cup sugar and yeast to half of water.
Mix eggs and oil.
Add all dry ingredients, egg mixture and water together and let rise for 1 hour.
Roll out.
Bake at 400° until done.
Makes about 30 rolls.

title: joyce's oven made caramel corn
directions: Spread freshly popped corn in a large, shallow sheet pan. Put it in a low oven, 250°, to keep warm and crisp.

Combine butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart heavy saucepan. Place over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves. Continue to boil to the firm-ball stage (about 5 minutes). Remove from heat and stir in baking soda.
Syrup will foam.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese.
Add dry jello to pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and mix all together.

title: chocolate-peanut butter sundaes
directions: Mix peanut butter and chocolate syrup until smooth.
Serve on scoops of vanilla ice cream.

title: dirt cake
directions: In one bowl, mix together the first 3 ingredients.
In a second bowl, mix together the milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Fold both mixtures together.
In a medium size plastic flowerpot, layer the Oreos, then pudding until pot is full.
On the top, use the 12 Oreo cookies only; these must be grated fine.
Place a plastic or silk poinsettia or any flower in the pot and you have a special Christmas present or unique birthday gift.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream 1 cup peanut butter, 1/3 to 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into graham cracker pie shell.
Top with 1/3 cup peanut butter and 1/3 to 1/2 cup confectioners sugar.
Use just enough sugar to make mixture crumbly.
Spoon over pie. Refrigerate.

title: chinese wedding rings
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour, salt, nuts, water and vanilla.
Dough is dry.
Press into balls the size of large olives.
Bake on ungreased cookie pans in slow oven (300°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: stir-fry venison
directions: Cut steak into small strips.
Flour and brown in oil.
Add soy sauce, bell pepper and onions and any other vegetables such as broccoli, carrots, etc.
Add barbecue sauce and water as needed. Cook and stir on high setting until vegetables have reached the desired tenderness.

title: cheese balls(appetizers)
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Put a piece of cheese and a piece of pepper on each.
Pinch together to close edges.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Makes a great appetizer for kids.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water until tender.
Drain thoroughly.
In a large skillet, saute onion in 5 tablespoons butter until tender.
Add soup and mix well.
Add cheese.
Heat and stir until melted.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in cabbage, salt and pepper. Transfer to an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.

title: crane breast chili
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight in water 2 inches above beans. Simmer, covered, until tender.
Add tomato juice and chopped tomatoes.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Saute green peppers and onion in oil.
Add to beans.
Saute meat and add to beans.
Add spices and simmer 2 hours.
Remove lid and simmer 30 minutes more.

title: spam casserole
directions: Repeat layers until your casserole dish is full.
Add a little milk in each corner of dish so it doesn't stick.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Layer a 1-quart casserole with sliced potatoes and diced onion.
Heat can of cheese soup and water until well blended. Pour over potatoes and onion.
Slice margarine over top and sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Uncover the last 30 minutes and lightly lift potatoes up through casserole.

title: chocolate eclaire
directions: Mix pudding according to box.
Blend in sour cream and cool whip.
Layer in dish starting with crackers, pudding, crackers, pudding until dish is full.
Final layer crackers.
Put icing in microwave for about 30 seconds or until pourable.
Pour chocolate on top and put in refrigerator until chocolate is set.

title: vegetable spread
directions: Can use for sandwich or spread on ham slice with cheese stick in center for ham roll-up, about 1/2-inch slice, place on cucumber slice.

title: scalloped mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and cut into small pieces.
Put in bowl.
Crush crackers over the mushrooms.
Season and pour milk over mushrooms and crackers.
Mix and pour into buttered casserole.
Dot with margarine and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: festive pina colada cheesecake
directions: Stir together butter, graham cracker crumbs, pecans and 1 tablespoon sugar and press into bottom and 1 1/2-inches up sides of a lightly greased 10-inch spring-form pan. Beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar at medium speed with an electric mixer 3 minutes or until fluffy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Add pineapple and next 4 ingredients, beating until blended. Pour mixture into crust. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool on a wire rack. Spread Glaze over top of cheesecake. Cover and chill at least 8 hours. Garnish, if desired. Makes 1 (10-inch) cheesecake.

title: dorothy's cheese log
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients and form into log.
Roll cheese log in 1/2 teaspoon chili powder, 1/2 teaspoon paprika and 1/4 cup finely chopped pecans.
Wrap log with plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions and pour on top of coconut and pecan mixture.

title: rotini with shrimp
directions: Put Zatarain's Shrimp 'n Crab Boil in a medium pot of water and boil for about 4 minutes.
Add shrimp and boil for 2 minutes. Remove shrimp and save the water.
Add noodles to the water and cook until tender.
Strain.
In a large bowl combine noodles, bell pepper, celery, olives, shrimp and mushrooms.
Add vinegar, Hellmann's dressing and salt and pepper to taste.
Toss and serve. Easy to make and very delicious.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add cheese, sour cream and spices. Reserve some cheese for the top.
Place mixture on tortillas; roll up.
Place in a greased baking pan.
Mix chili with a little water.
Pour over the top.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Stuff chilies with Monterey Jack cheese.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese between layers (if necessary).
Combine milk and eggs. Blend.
Combine salt, pepper, paprika and flour.
Add to milk and egg mixture.
Pour chili mix in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Blend flour, sugar and margarine, add nuts and spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 - 20 minutes and let cool.
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and cool whip until smooth, spread over crust.
Blend instant lemon pudding and milk until thick and spread over mixture.
Spread remaining cool whip on top and sprinkle with nuts if desired.

title: italian pizzelles
directions: In electric mixer, beat eggs; add sugar gradually.
Mix in cooled melted margarine and flavoring.
Add flour and baking powder and beat well.
Put 1 teaspoon of batter on pizzelle iron and bake until golden brown.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Combine squash and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut Crisco into flour until well blended.
Stir in warm water to make a dough.
When
all gathers together so that the bowl is left clean,
dump
onto well-floured surface and knead until very stiff.
Put in
bowl.
Cover
and
chill.
Roll out dough on well-floured surface until very thin (1/8-inch).
Cut into 1-inch wide strips.
Bring
broth to rolling boil.
Pinch strips into 2-inch pieces
and	drop into boiling broth.
Turn down to simmer. Add chopped chicken and cover.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix these dry ingredients thoroughly in very large container. Use about 1/3 cup mix.
Fill mug with hot water.
Stir or mix in blender.
Makes 30 or more servings.

title: outlaw deer stew
directions: Dump all ingredients in a large crock-pot.
Add enough water to cover well.
Stir slightly to mix ingredients.
Cook on low for 8 hours or overnight.
(Taste during last hour of cooking time to make sure you have enough salt.
If not, add it at this time.) Meat and vegetables should all be very tender, because it's so good you won't take time to chew!

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream until creamy.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Spread taco sauce on top of mixture evenly.
Layer scallions, tomatoes, lettuce and cheese in order. Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pan-fried trout with bacon
directions: Crisp bacon in skillet; remove from pan.
Keep warm.
Season the inside of the fish with salt and pepper; dredge in flour. Pan-fry the fish in bacon fat until golden brown on both sides. Drain on absorbent paper.
Use bacon pieces as a garnish with lemon wedges and deep fried parsley.
Makes 10 portions.

title: stollen (authentic german coffee cake)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in mixer bowl. Add sugar, salt, eggs, yolk, butter and half of flour. Beat 10 minutes at medium speed on mixer or by hand. Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often with spoon. Blend in rest of flour, nuts, fruits and rind. Scrape batter from sides of bowl. Cover with cloth and let rise in warm place (85°) until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir down batter by beating 25 strokes.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: grannie's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before baking approximately 1 hour.
Roll into small balls, then roll in sugar. Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: pound cake
directions: Ice with lemon glaze or chocolate frosting.

title: german salad
directions: Slice cabbage, not
too thin.
Slice peppers and onions in onion ring style.
Add
pimentos to mixture.
Boil vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and seed
about 1 minute.
Pour over and stir gradually.
Let set 4 hours or longer if possible in refrigerator.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine shortening, peanut butter, salt, eggs, milk and vanilla. Mix well; add flour, baking soda and sugar. Shape dough into balls; roll in sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from oven.
Place chocolate kiss on top of cookie; press down in center.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Puree all ingredients.	Store in glass container.

title: anasazia beans(great low-fat dish)
directions: Put washed beans in a large crock-pot or saucepan. Boil 30 minutes and let stand (away from heat) 1 hour. Drain water and rinse beans.
(This step helps with digestability.) Add water to cover beans, plus 1 to 2-inches more.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour on stovetop or 4 to 6 hours in crock-pot on low.

title: pepperoni pizza bread(bread machine)
directions: Place all ingredients in bread machine except pepperoni.
Add pepperoni in when raisin/nut signal beeps or 5 to 10 minutes before last kneading cycle ends.
Select basic/white bread cycle and use medium or light crust.
Yeast amount is correct.

title: strawberry creme salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients well.
Keeps well in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix together dry ingredients. Add milk and blend.
Put fruit in dish.
Add the dough on top. Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes or until dough is done.

title: homemade shake and bake(healthy mixes u-make)
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in a sealable container or zip lock plastic bag. This will keep up to 4 months in the pantry, depending on the humidity (you may just want to keep it in the freezer). This recipe will double or triple well.

title: deviled tuna
directions: Mix the butter or margarine in saucepan.
Add the flour; blend well.
Pour into a buttered baking dish or into individual dishes. Cover with bread crumbs or crackers mixed with 2 tablespoons melted butter or margarine.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes, or until brown.
Serves 4.

title: cream filled cupcakes
directions: Prepare and bake cupcakes according to package directions, using paper-lined muffin cups. Cool for 5 minutes before removing to wire racks to cool completely.

title: diabetic flower garden cake(calories: 186)
directions: Beat egg yolk and mix well with the lemon juice and water. Cook a few minutes in a double boiler until the mixture coats a spoon.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Mix well and put in airtight container.
Use 1 spoonful per cup of hot water or more if you like stronger taste.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix Stove Top stuffing mix according to package.
Place in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Next, layer chicken, mix soups together and pour over chicken.
Layer cheese.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Place on top.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Let stand in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a large bowl.
Add corn syrup and milk.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High 5 to 7 minutes. Mixture should be hot and bubbly.
Stir well.
Microwave, uncovered, at Medium-high 13 to 17 minutes or until mixture reaches soft ball stage (235°).
Add butter but do not stir.
Let cool.
Add vanilla and beat until candy is stiff.
Stir in pecans and pour onto a greased 8-inch or 9-inch plate or platter. Yields 1 pound.

title: hawaiian chicken(do ahead)
directions: Combine butter, soy sauce, lime juice and lime rind.
Marinate chicken pieces in marinade several hours, turning 2 or 3 times. Bake at 400° for 1 hour, basting while baking.
Turns golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix well until well blended and chill.
Makes about 1 pint.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: grilled ranch steaks
directions: Combine juices, water, sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour over steaks, allow to stand 4 to 6 hours out of refrigerator.
Turn occasionally.
Grill over hot fire 3 to 4 minutes on each side for rare.
Increase cooking time for medium or well done.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls in 3 oblong widths of pan and 1 longways across the bottom.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly brown.
Mix the cream cheese and dressing until creamy.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with vegetables and cheese last.

title: benedictine cheese spread
directions: Peel and grate the cucumber, down to the seed (do not use seed).

title: texas cornbread casserole
directions: Mix the batter (first 8 ingredients) together.
Add corn; set aside.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour 1/2 the batter mixture into pan.
Then layer meat, cheese, onion and peppers.
Add the other 1/2 of the batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except poppy seed until well blended. Stir in poppy seed.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: stewed rice and pigeon peas
directions: Saute ham and salt pork; add peppers, tomatoes, onion and garlic.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Add capers, olives, achote coloring or substitute with sazon goya and pigeon peas.
Mix well and let cool for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add rice.
Mix well and add the water and salt to taste.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover and cook slowly until the liquid has evaporated on medium heat.
Rice takes approximately 25 minutes to cook.
Serve hot.
Buen apetito.

title: kiebel's americanized lasagne
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Add ground beef and brown.
Remove excess oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, and spices.
Stir to blend and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Preheat oven. Layer noodles, swiss cheese, cottage cheese, and meat mixture. Repeat 2 more times.
Sprinkle Parmesan generously and bake.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: pink pickled eggs
directions: Hard boil eggs. Bring all other ingredients to a boil, then simmer 10 minutes.
Pour boiling beets and juice over peeled (hot) eggs.
Cover and refrigerate three days before serving.

title: pork and rice casserole
