directions: Brown pork chops.
Season with garlic powder, salt and pepper. While the pork chops are browning, mix the rice with the remaining ingredients and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Put the browned chops on top of the rice.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
This dish can be made into a rice casserole by replacing the pork chops with a 1/2 stick of butter or margarine.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Bring tomatoes and sugar to boil (10 minutes), stirring. Remove from heat.
Add jello.
Put into jars; seal with wax.

title: to die for pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let cool.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Mix in pecans and coconut.
Brown until golden.
Remove from heat and let cool.
In a bowl, mix together the cream cheese, condensed milk and Cool Whip.

title: crock pot apple butter
directions: Wash, core and quarter apples, but do not peel.
Combine apples and cider in lightly oiled crock pot or slow cooker. Cover, cook on high for about 3 hours until tender.
Sieve apples. For each pint of sieved fruit, add 1 cup sugar, 1 tsp. cinnamon, 1/2 tsp. allspice, and 1/2 tsp. cloves.
Stir often and well. Cook until it suits, after 2 hours, remove lid to allow fruit to cool down.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion and green pepper in a large bowl. Add sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Mix well.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Wait 24 hours before eating.
These will keep about 3 months.

title: blue ribbon fudge
directions: In a thick saucepan or iron skillet, cook to a soft ball stage the butter, sugar, Karo, chocolate and milk.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and beat with electric mixer until thick.
Spread quickly in buttered 6 x 8-inch dish (not 9 x 13-inch).
You can add chopped walnuts (1/2 cup) if you like.

title: fried irish potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes into 1/2-inch strips and cover with water. Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Put mixture into small bag.
Remove potatoes from water, but do not blot.
Drop a few slices at a time into the bag and shake.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: deli macaroni salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain. Rinse with cold water and drain.

title: harrington punch
directions: Chill juice and nectar almost to a freeze.
Combine with remaining ingredients in punch bowl.

title: veal luncheon meat(kalv sylta lungmos)
directions: Put 3 to 4 pound beef tongue in large kettle or pot having a tight-fitting cover.
Add boiling water to cover the tongue.
(Add more water during cooking to keep tongue covered.)
When tongue is tender, slit skin on underside and peel it off.
Cut away roots and gristle.
(Plunging it in cold water after cooking helps to loosen the skin.) Return tongue to cooking liquid to complete cooling.
When cool, drain and chill in refrigerator.
Cut chilled tongue into thin slices and arrange on a serving platter.
Garnish with whole apple and celery leaves.
Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Put cleaned berries into pie shell.
Mix other ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour over berries using fork to make sure berries are coated.
Cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: dutch potato salad
directions: Chop bacon and fry crisp.
Remove from pan and set aside. Saute onion in the fat.
Add water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes and parsley and heat through.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Serve warm.

title: mushroom treat
directions: Rinse and remove stems from mushrooms.
Place on a Pyrex plate, hollow side up.
Into the center of each mushroom, put garlic salt and butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Prepare rice.
Saute onion and celery in oleo until tender.
Mix all ingredients, except Cheez Whiz.
Pour in casserole and top with Cheez Whiz.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: mexican salad
directions: Prepare lettuce as for any toss salad.
Drain and wash chilled beans.
Add beans, tomatoes, onion, grated cheese and dressing to lettuce.
Chill 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving.
Add corn chips just before serving.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and flour; cream until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and salt.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: baked swiss green beans
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Blend in flour; add onion, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in sour cream.
Cook until smooth and well blended.
Stir in 1 cup cheese until melted.
Place beans in 1-quart baking dish.
Pour sauce over beans.
Sprinkle with remaining cup of cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken ala orange
directions: Brown chicken breast in butter.
Arrange in shallow baking dishes.
Pour remaining butter over chicken.
Arrange orange slices or drained mandarin oranges on chicken pieces.
Pour wine over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt into large bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Stir egg with orange rind and orange juice.
Then blend mixture into flour mixture.
Stir just until flour is moistened.
Fold in raisins, cranberries and nuts.
Spoon into greased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 75 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls in a cookie sheet; bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: banana cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions. Add oil in water while cooking. Drain pasta and allow to cool. Mix and beat mayonnaise, milk, sugar and vinegar together. Add vegetables, salt and pepper. Mix together; then fold in cold pasta.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all beans; bring to a boil vinegar, oil and sugar.
Pour over beans with onions while hot.
Chill overnight.
If you like, cucumber and green pepper may be added.
Also, I like to use purple onions for taste and color.

title: kiffles
directions: Place flour in large bowl.
With pastry blender, cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg yolks and sour cream.
Stir until combined.
Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead until dough is smooth and can be shaped into ball.
If sticky, add more flour.
Refrigerate dough until ready to use.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix by hand.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Pat slightly and place pecan half on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: italian beef pie
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain well.
Cook and drain broccoli. Combine meat, broccoli, soup and sour cream.
Season to taste.
(I use a hint of garlic powder.)
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole; top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 generously.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Place chili in saucepan.
Add 2 cans of water to make it watery.
Bring to a boil.
Slip corn tortillas into chili until soft (not too long or they will tear).
Take out.
Place on rectangular glass or aluminum baking pan.
Stuff with cheese and a small amount of onion.
Onion is optional.
Roll tortillas and place them in a row, side by side.
Start a new row on top after bottom of pan is filled.
Place rest of chili on top and add grated cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Serves 12.

title: sour milk griddle cakes
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure.
Add baking soda, salt and sugar and sift again.
Add milk, egg and shortening and mix.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peaches-n-cream
directions: In 13 x 9-inch oblong dish, layer with vanilla wafers, drained canned peaches and Cool Whip.
Top with toasted pecans.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: gourmet fruit mold
directions: Chill several hours.
Stir well before serving.

title: smothered pork chop
directions: Wash pork chops, batter in flour, put in baking pan or bowl with cover on.
Add just a little black pepper, a little Accent, a little Italian seasoning and a little celery salt.
Mix flour and other ingredients together and put in baking pan.
Pour water in the bowl and some butter or margarine and let cook until done.

title: brandi's seafood bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips and paprika. Place in a casserole dish.
Top with potato chips and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: southern chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine; brown chicken, onion and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish and add rice, soup, bouillon and water.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: crayfish etouffees
directions: Combine flour and oil in a microwave-safe dish.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until roux is light brown.
Add onions, green onions, bell peppers and garlic.
Stir and microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Transfer to a 3-quart dish and add tomatoes, crayfish tails, fat, lemon juice, crab boil, Tabasco, salt, pepper and water.
Mix well and microwave on Medium for 5 to 6 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.
(Best ever!)

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and add pretzels.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° in 9 X 13 pan.
Cool.
Cream: cream cheese and sugar.
Add cool whip.
Spread mixture over pretzels.
Mix jello and boiling water. Add frozen strawberries.
Let jello partially set before pouring over cheese mixture.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Drain strawberries.
Add enough water to juice to make 2 1/2 cups.
Add juice, pudding, jello and tapioca together.
Heat on high until boiling.
Cool and stir.
Add strawberries, bananas, Cool Whip and pineapple (if desired).
Chill.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Beat eggs with evaporated milk. Add melted butter. Pour over macaroni. Blend in 3 cups of cheese. Spray crock-pot with Pam. Put ingredients in crock-pot. Add 1 cup cheese to top. Cover and cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours. DO NOT REMOVE LID DURING COOKING. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cynthia's grandma's biscuits
directions: Sift flour and sugar. Cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to buttermilk and pour into flour mixture. Knead lightly. Pinch off biscuits as needed. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes. Can be stored in refrigerator up to 2 weeks, wrapped tightly.

title: t-cakes
directions: Mix flour and sugar, then add egg, shortening and vanilla. Mix well.
Add pecans.
Roll into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until very light brown.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine sugar and cream cheese. Mix well by hand. Add Cool Whip in large bowl. Pour into crust and chill at least 30 minutes. Pour pie filling onto cake and chill.

title: salmon pie
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes as you usually do with milk.
It's a good way to use leftover potatoes.
Chop onion fine; add 1 egg, salt and pepper to taste.
I don't use salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and top with second crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until golden color.
Serve with creamed peas.
An excellent meal.

title: rice pudding(arrozo doce #1)
directions: In a heavy saucepan stir rice into boiling water and add salt. Boil for about 10 minutes.
Stir in sugar and add milk and lemon peel if desired.
Continue cooking, stirring frequently, until rice mixture thickens, about 15 minutes longer.
Beat the eggs and stir in about 5 tablespoons of the rice mixture.
Lower the heat and quickly add egg mixture to the simmering rice.
Stir constantly and cook 10 minutes longer or until thick and creamy. If desired, add vanilla extract at this time and pour onto serving platter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: dad's dill bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, dill, salt, margarine and warmed cottage cheese to yeast mixture.
Add 1/2 cup flour and beat 3 minutes in blender.
Add rest of flour.
Mix well with hands.

title: cucumber and carrot relish
directions: Mix salt with ground vegetables.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain off liquid.
Boil vinegar and sugar for 3 minutes.
Put seeds in a cheesecloth bag and float in kettle with vinegar and sugar mixture. Drain vegetables and add to vinegar and sugar mixture.
Remove the bag of seeds.
Cook for 30 minutes on low heat.
Put in sterilized pint jars and seal.

title: mom's quick lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in saucepan, stirring until crumbly.
Add soup mix, tomato sauce and 1 cup of water, mixing well.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: diabetic apple cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the dates, apples, raisins and water.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Combine the dry ingredients; stir into the apple mixture, then combine the eggs with sweetener.
Mix well; add to the batter.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto a nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; remove and debone.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Mix soups with chicken and spaghetti.
tags: cream of onion soup or another can cream of chicken

title: murphy pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan or cookie sheet. Line with wax paper.
Grease and flour paper.
Sift first 6 ingredients.
Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in pumpkin, then stir in sifted ingredients.
Pour onto prepared pan and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Loosen around edges with knife and invert onto clean damp cloth sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Peel off wax paper and trim 1/4 inch from cake edges.
Roll cake in towel from short end.
Place seamed-side down on rack to cool.
Continue with Cream Cheese Filling.

title: bobbie's brownies
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Combine in bowl sugar, flour, butter and cocoa.
Beat until well mixed.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat after each.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in pan and cook for about 35 minutes at 275°.
I usually double recipe (takes 50 minutes for double recipe).

title: romanian bean soup
directions: Soak lima beans 5-6 hours or overnight.
Drain beans and rinse well to remove any loose shells.
Place beans in crockpot with 8 cups of water, chopped onion, carrot, garlic and bouillon cube. Cover and cook on low for 18 hours or until beans are tender.
Heat 2 Tbsp. oil in a skillet and saut diced onions until browned.
Add onions to bean soup and stir.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 8 servings.

title: jay's favorite cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Add salt and sugars.
Beat until batter has glossy look.
Fold in nuts.
Grease cookies pans. Drop tablespoon of batter onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Beat egg whites until they hold soft peaks. Gradually add sugar until thick. Add salt, cream of tartar and almond extract and beat until shiny and thick. Fold in cracker crumbs, pecans and dates. Pour into 2 greased pie shells. Bake 45 minutes, until lightly golden.

title: refrigerator yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 3 tablespoons sugar in 1/3 cup warm water and let stand 45 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat together well.
Let raise double in bulk, then put in refrigerator. Cover with damp cloth or loosely with wax paper until ready to make rolls.
Then take part of dough; make into rolls and put remainder of dough back into refrigerator until needed.
Let rolls raise to double in size or about 2 hours.
Bake in 400° oven about 15 minutes.
Grease rolls with butter.

title: mom's peach pie with self-crust
directions: Cut peaches into pie pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over peaches plus 1/4 cup water.
Mix melted oleo, 1/2 cup sugar and flour. Add vanilla and ground cinnamon; mix.
Pour over peaches and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: o' henry bars
directions: Stir the white sugar and corn syrup until dissolves.
Boil it less than 1 minute; remove from heat.
Add the peanut butter to this mixture.
Pour this mixture over the cereal; mix well. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
In a double boiler, melt the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread over mixture. Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.
Let chocolate harden. Cut into squares.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Separate eggs, placing whites in one large bowl and yellows in another large bowl.
Let whites warm to room temperature, about 1 hour.
Grease 10-inch tube pan with electric beater at high speed.
Beat egg yolks with shortening and margarine until well blended.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add extracts, beat until blended.
At low speed, beat in flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add coconut, beat until well blended.
Beat egg whites just until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold whites into batter until well combined.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 2 hours, or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan or wire rack for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly on wire rack.
Dust top with 10x sugar.

title: arizona stacks
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas with a mixer. Spread thinly on each tortilla and layer them, topping with 1 tortilla not spread with mixture. Chill overnight. Cut on the diagonal to make bite-size pieces.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind up pears in food processor.
Add all other ingredients. Mix well.
After it starts boiling, boil for 30 minutes and seal in jars.

title: dannon brownies(makes 24 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Batter will be very thick.
Spread in pan 9 x 13-inch and bake for 22 to 24 minutes or 9 x 9-inch or 8
x 8-inch for 32 to 34 minutes.
Cool before cutting.	Makes 24 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread evenly in a greased 9-inch square baking pan cherry pie filling.
Over this, sprinkle cake mix.
Drizzle over all margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve warm.
If desired, sprinkle with chopped nuts, flaked coconut or top with ice cream.

title: delicious potato salad bake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Butter or grease one 8X16 inch baking dish.
Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.
Add potatoes and cook until tender but still firm, about 15 minutes. Drain and cool.
Place bacon in a large, deep skillet, cook over medium high heat until evenly brown.
Add onions, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Cook until onions and mushrooms are soft.
Slice potatoes and place a thin layer in the baking dish.
Follow with a layer of the bacon mixture and repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Pour cream and milk over layers; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake for approximately 35 minutes, or until cream and milk have almost reduced completely.

title: raw ground beef casserole
directions: Layer ground beef on bottom of 9 x 11-inch or smaller casserole dish. Cut onion in pieces; layer over ground beef. Layer cream of chicken and cream of celery soup over onions. Cover with Tater Tots. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: chicken fingers with honey mustard
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2 x 2-inch strips.

title: beverly's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil and pumpkin together.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to liquid mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: almond curried fruit
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle fruit with almonds.
Combine butter, brown sugar and curry powder.
Top fruit with brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons syrup.
Drain cherries.

In top of double boiler, heat egg yolks slightly; add reserved pineapple syrup, the vinegar, sugar, salt and butter. Place over hot (not boiling) water; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens slightly and barely coats a spoon (about 12 minutes).
Cool to room temperature.
Combine well drained oranges, pineapple, cherries and the marshmallows.
Pour custard over and mix gently.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into serving bowl.
Cover and chill 24 hours.
Trim with fresh fruit.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mocha brownie torte
directions: Bake brownie mix as directed in two round pans.
Bake about 5 minutes less than directions (approximately 15 to 20 minutes). Mix Cool Whip, instant coffee and brown sugar very well.
Spread over brownie layers; top with almonds.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend in blender the shortening, sugar, milk and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Test with toothpick to see if baked enough.

title: hot fudge
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil, slowly.
Let boil one minute.
Add vanilla.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meats together.
Add bread crumbs, then milk.
Add all other ingredients, except catsup, flour and water.
Shape into a loaf.
Put loaf into a greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven.
Add flour to pan, stirring to mix with fat.
Add water; mix.
Pour catsup over top of loaf.
Return to oven for gravy to thicken.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice. Serves 6.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour a 12 cup Bundt pan or a 10 inch tube pan.
In a large bowl, combine granulated sugar and margarine; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add powdered sugar; blend well.
By hand, stir in flour, cocoa and walnuts until well blended.
Spoon batter into pan; spread evenly.
Bake 58 to 62 minutes.
Since the cake has a soft filling, an ordinary doneness test cannot be used.
Cool upright in pan on wire rack 1 hour; invert onto serving plate.
Cool completely.
In a small bowl, combine 3/4 cup powdered sugar, 1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa and enough milk to reach desired drizzling consistency, usually 4 to 6 teaspoons.
Spoon over top of cake, allowing some to run down the sides.
Store tightly covered.
Makes 16 servings.

title: baked corn
directions: Scrape kernels and juice from ears of corn.
Combine corn, salt, pepper, eggs, and milk; mixing well.
Spoon into greased 1 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375 degrees for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix well and freeze.

title: old fashion fudge
directions: Melt over low heat.
Bring to a boil and cook for 1 minute or until mixture will make a soft ball in water.
Remove and beat until mixture crackles while beating.
Pour in nuts.
Pour into well buttered platter or pan.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish arrange crushed cookies.
Spread softened ice cream over crushed cookies.
Next pour topping over ice cream.
Top with Cool Whip and pecans.
Freeze until hard. Before serving, let set at room temperature about 20 minutes.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until smooth.
Stir in asparagus.
Cook 1 minute stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk.
Heat until bubbly.

title: crock-pot cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chocolate chips. Once mixed, add chips.
Put in crock-pot that has been lightly sprayed. Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or high for 3 to 4 hours. Serve warm with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Make cake by directions on box.
Make 2 layers.
Mix cream cheese, sugars, and Cool Whip together.
Spread on cake layers. Top with pie filling.
Spread filling on sides and top of cake. Top with pie filling.

title: cashew cole slaw
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: decadent french toast
directions: The night before, combine corn syrup, brown sugar and margarine in a small, heavy saucepan.
Heat, stirring, until bubbly.
Pour syrup mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Nestle the bread slices into the syrup, making 2 layers.
Mix together eggs, cinnamon, milk and vanilla.
Pour over the bread.
Cover pan and refrigerate overnight.

title: ridge runners apple custard pie
directions: Stew up dried apples and sweeten to taste.
Add enough milk to soften apples.
Mash into pulp.
Add egg yolk, cornstarch, flavor with vanilla.
Cook until slightly thick.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325°.
Sprinkle with cinnamon before baking. Bake until it has a solid consistency.

title: foundation cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done in long cake pan.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water in pan.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved, then cook to 260°.
Remove and pour in a thin stream into beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until hard enough to pour out.

title: southern barbecue
directions: Roast the pork for 2 hours at 350°.
Remove and cut up into small pieces (remove any fat).
Add can of tomato soup.
Cut up onion and add it.
Mix the brown sugar, wine vinegar and barbecue sauce (to taste).
Stir all ingredients.
Bake for 2 hours in covered casserole dish at 325° to 350°.
When done, mash with potato masher.
Serve with cole slaw on large warm buns (optional).

title: 5 bean salad
directions: Brown the sausage, onion and green pepper together in skillet. In a large baking bowl, add the remaining ingredients.
Add the sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This is delicious!

title: easy to make cut-out cookies
directions: Mix well and roll out on lightly floured pastry sheet.
Cut into shapes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Decorate as desired.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen cookies, depending on size of cutters.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk. Put flour and sugar in a large bowl and mix well. Dissolve yeast in water and add to milk mixture; mix well. Add oil and mix again. Cover with wet warm cup towel and leave about 1 hour or until doubled in bulk. Punch down. Pinch off some and place on floured board. Add enough flour to make pliable. Roll out and cut. Place in oiled pan and let rise for 1 hour. Bake at 450° until done.

title: spoon bread
directions: Combine meal, salt and cold milk.
Add to scalded milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Stir a small amount of corn meal mixture into beaten egg yolks, then return to corn meal mixture.
Mix well, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart souffle dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes (do not open oven door).
Serve immediately with lots of butter.

title: seven layer mexican dip
directions: Peel and
mash	the
avocado with the lemon juice.
Mix the sour
cream,
mayonnaise
and
taco mix together.
Spread beans on a large plate, then layer the rest of the ingredients in order given.
Best
if
chilled several hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Cut baked potatoes in half; scoop out potato and mash well. Combine with sour cream, butter, cheese, soup mix, bacon bits, salt and pepper. Fill potato shells and sprinkle with paprika. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken angels
directions: Marinate chicken in eggs for 2 hours.
Coat with bread crumbs. Brown in margarine.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 mushrooms, then cover with cheese.
Then top with mushrooms.
Pour broth over top.

title: bakers clay
directions: Knead the ingredients.
Form into whatever shape you desire. Bake at 350° until edges are brown.
Paint.
This is nonedible. It is for decoration or craft purposes.

title: low-fat german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Remove and crumble bacon.
Drain skillet, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings.
Saute onions in reserved drippings in skillet until tender.
Stir in flour.
Add vinegar and water.
Cook until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in sugar, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and bacon; mix gently.
Cook just until heated through. Serve warm.
May add boiled eggs, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Pour into a large greased pan. Sprinkle top with 1 cup brown sugar and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: picante potato pie
directions: Combine all but bacon.
Mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Remove; sprinkle with bacon.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Serve with Picante sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chili in a hurry!(microwave chili)
directions: Combine beef and onion in a 3-quart casserole.
Cover with lid; microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir; re-cover and continue cooking on High for 4 minutes or more, until beef is browned. Drain fat!
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover and microwave on High for 7 to 10 minutes, or until mixture is hot. Uncover; stir well, re-cover and continue at 50% power (Medium) for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: maizie's christmas cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and dried beef; mix well with cream cheese.
Form into ball; roll in chopped pecans.
Allow cheese ball to age in refrigerator for at least 3 days before serving.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Store in an airtight container.

title: creamy leek soup
directions: Wash leeks very well and chop fine.
Saute with butter.
Mash all ingredients and add light cream and milk.
Simmer.
Serve topped with sour cream, chives or parsley.

title: cinnamon roll-ups
directions: Flatten bread slices with rolling pin.
Mix cheese, egg yolk and 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread 1 tablespoon on each slice of bread. Roll up tightly.
Mix remaining cinnamon and sugar.
Brush rollups with butter.
Roll each piece of bread in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place on cookie sheet.
Chill for 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Cut each piece diagonally in three pieces.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter with poppy seed added. Pour butter mixture over the crackers. Mix chicken, sour cream, soup and 1 cup chicken broth. Line casserole with cracker crumbs (save enough for top). Pour chicken mixture over this and top with cracker crumbs. Bake until bubbly (about 45 minutes) at 350°.

title: camp fried duck
directions: Fillet duck breast and beat each one thoroughly; salt and pepper to taste.
Go a little heavy on the pepper.
Shake or roll in flour.
Have coals very hot.
Place frypan on coals; put oil (about 1-inch) in pan.
Place fillets in oil.
Cook until brown. Do not overcook; 4 or 5 minutes will do if oil is very hot.
Turn once.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Roll out crescent rolls and separate.
Slice lengthwise partly through each hot dog.
Stuff with 1/2 slice cheese.
Roll in crescent roll from wide end.
Bake as directed for the rolls.

title: quick veal parmigiana
directions: Pound veal as thin as possible.
Brown in butter 5 to 7 minutes on each side.
Remove from skillet.
Combine tomato puree and seasonings in same skillet.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring until thoroughly heated.
Remove from heat; push sauce to side of skillet, topping with slices of cheese.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Blend bread crumbs, grated cheese and melted butter. Sprinkle over sauce.
Broil about 4-inches from heat for 3 to 5 minutes or until crumbs are lightly brown.
Serve immediately. Serves 6.

title: pork 'n' beans casserole
directions: Fry bacon leaving grease in skillet.
Add chopped bell pepper and saute until wilted look.
Add bread and let soak up grease. Add crumbled up bacon.
Add pork and beans.
Top with cheese slices.
When cheese is melted, serve.
(Good with French fries or just by itself.)

title: jalapeno squash croquettes
directions: Cook squash and onion together in salted water until tender; drain thoroughly.
Crumble muffins and add to squash.
Beat egg in a large bowl.
Add squash and corn bread crumbs.
Beat together thoroughly.
Heat oil in deep fat fryer until very hot.
Take squash mixture by big spoonfuls and roll in bread crumbs on wax paper.
Drop into fryer.
Cook, 4 at a time, about 3 or 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
These are good frozen and reheated.

title: easy as cherry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour the cherry pie filling into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Spread evenly on bottom.
Then sprinkle cake mix over the pie filling.
Do not pat down.
Melt margarine.
Pour evenly over cake mix.
Bake 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: beet salad
directions: Add beet juice to sugar.
Heat to boiling to melt sugar and jello.
Mix with beets.
Add 2 tablespoons horseradish and mold as desired.

title: divinity
directions: In
a
2 quart saucepan, combine sugar, Karo syrup, 1/4 teaspoon salt
and
cup
water.
Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Beat
egg whites to stiff peaks.
Pour syrup into egg whites slowly, beating continuously.
Beat until mixture looks dull and
holds its shape.
Add nuts and cherries, if desired. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: miniature meatballs
directions: Combine the soy sauce, water, minced garlic and nutmeg in a bowl; stir to blend.
Add the ground meat; mix lightly but thoroughly.
Form into meatballs 1 inch in diameter.
Arrange in a lightly oiled baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Place on a heated tray or in a chafing dish.
Serve with toothpicks.
Makes 24 meatballs.

title: corn fritters
directions: Blend together the milk and egg.
Add gradually to pancake mix. Stir in sugar.
Stir in corn and raisins.
Heat enough vegetable oil in deep frypan to float corn fritters.
Drop from tablespoon into hot oil; do not crowd.
Fry fritters 3 to 5 minutes; drain on paper toweling.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove and put Swiss cheese on top.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: bread pudding with whiskey sauce
directions: Scald milks; add bread and let stand until cool.
Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla and butter.
Combine the bread-milk mixture.
Bake in greased 2-quart casserole for one hour at 350°.
Serve with Whiskey Sauce.

title: broccoli casserole 3
directions: Saute onion in 1/2 stick margarine.
Cook and drain broccoli. Add rice and remaining margarine to onion.
Add soup.
Use salt and pepper to taste.
Put cooked broccoli into baking dish.
Pour rice and soup mixture over broccoli.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: cinnamon sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Combine in another bowl the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Mix and add to sugar mixture.
Mix and refrigerate.
Form into small balls, then roll in sugar mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook to a hard-ball stage sugar, water, corn syrup, salt and margarine, then add vanilla and pour over popped corn.
Butter hands and make into balls.
Food coloring may be added for colored balls.
Makes 12 to 15.

title: raisin drops
directions: Beat the eggs, sugar and butter for 10 minutes.
Add the rest in the order given.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a moderate oven about 10 minutes.

title: stag chili(microwave)
directions: In 4-quart casserole, cook meat, green pepper and onion on High for 5 minutes, or until vegetables are tender, stirring once. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Cook on High for 15 minutes, stirring once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange beets
directions: Heat grated peel, orange and lemon juice in double boiler. Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add all at once and stir until thickened and clear.
Add butter or margarine and beets and heat in double boiler 15 to 20 minutes.
Slices of orange to garnish. Serves 4 to 6.

title: east indian spaghetti
directions: Brown meat, then add onions and brown.
Add rest of ingredients and cook about 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook 1/2 to 3/4 pound thin spaghetti.
Put cooked spaghetti in greased baking dish.
Add sauce and top with sliced cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Can be refrigerated and recommended because taste soaks in if made the day before.

title: orange fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all of the fruit; set aside.
In another bowl, combine dry pudding mix, milk and orange juice concentrate.
Beat until blended and thickened, approximately 2 minutes.
Fold in sour cream; fold into fruit mixture.
Cover and chill.
Garnish with kiwi fruit and strawberries.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into 2 large balls or 3 small balls.
Roll into crushed nuts and/or parsley flakes. Decorate with cherry on top.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: potato soup
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
In drippings; add onion and celery and cook until tender.
Stir in potatoes, water and mustard. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and soup; reheat but do not boil.
Add bacon and serve.

title: steak roulades
directions: Prepare mushroom stuffing.
Pound round steak very thin with a meat mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place 2 tablespoons stuffing on each piece.
Roll as for jelly roll; tie with butcher's string.
Coat with flour.
Brown several at a time on all sides in margarine in a Dutch oven for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: stuffed "armadillo" shells
directions: Cook hamburger meat in skillet with seasonings and a small amount of salt until done.
Cook broccoli with a small amount of water in microwave for about 8 minutes or until tender.
Then mix hamburger meat, soup and the cooked broccoli together.
Split the rolls a little and fill them with the meat stuffing.
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at about 375° for about 10 minutes or until done.

title: valentine cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a mixing bowl and add shortening. Combine milk and cherry juice in a separate cup.
Add 3/4 cup of liquid to dry ingredients.
Add flavorings and beat for 2 minutes. Add remaining liquid and egg whites; beat for 2 minutes.
Add cherries and nuts; blend.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour in a tube pan for 20 to 25 minutes for layers.

title: for a lasting marriage
directions: Blend above ingredients with your personalities and you and your spouse will have a marriage that will last forever through anything.
(To be served daily.)

title: brownie cake
directions: Grease well and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour and cocoa, mixed.
Beat well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
(I like to dredge my nuts with cocoa.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
As soon as baked, cover with marshmallows.
If they do not melt, return to oven until they do.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender, stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until smooth.
Cool and stir in milk with butter and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Heat for 1 minute.
Put potatoes in casserole dish, pour cheese sauce over potatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Put balance of cheese over, sprinkle crumbs and heat 15 minutes longer.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Saute pecans in butter in a skillet for 5 minutes or until toasted.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl, mixing well. Pour into 1 gallon ice cream freezer container.
Freeze for 10 minutes, using freezer directions.
Add pecans to ice cream mixture.
Freeze until firm.

title: blueberry-cream cheese squares
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, water and blueberries in saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened.
Cool.
Combine cracker crumbs and butter; press half the crumbs into bottom of foil-lined 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mash cream cheese until soft. Beat in sugar and vanilla gradually.
Fold in whipped topping; drop half the topping mix by spoonfuls over crumbs.
Spread gently with spatula.
Spread blueberry filling evenly over cheese mixture; spread with remaining cheese topping mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill overnight.
Use foil to remove dessert from pan.
Place dessert on platter; cut into squares. Yield:
15 servings.

title: boursin cheese dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: baked barbecued chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Place chicken in 10-inch square pan.
Cover with sauce. Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Stir and cook over medium heat until it boils.
Add the corn and the pimento.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add crumbled biscuits and, if desired, raisins, stirring well.
Spoon into lightly greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yields 9 servings.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir well.
Roll potatoes in flour.
Layer slices in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish. Top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg nog
directions: Blend well and enjoy!

title: two-tone cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello in 2 1/2 cups hot water.
Add the cranberry sauce.
Pour in mold or pan.
For second layer, drain pineapple and set aside.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 1/4 cup hot water.
Add small marshmallows.
Blend in the cream cheese and salt.
Add drained pineapple.
Mix well.
Chill until partially set, then fold in the Cool Whip or Dream Whip.
Pour over first layer.
Chill until firm.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and sour cream.
Add eggs and flavorings.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Fold into cream mixture and beat until smooth.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: ranch pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and peas as directed.
Rinse; drain and cool.
Fry bacon; drain; crumble.
Slice tomatoes in half.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Pour and mix salad dressing on salad shortly before serving.

title: italian chicken
directions: Sprinkle inside of chickens with Italian seasoning, rub salt and pepper on outside. Combine in bowl broth, water, wine, onion, and garlic. Put chickens in bake pan and pour liquid over the chicken. Place pats of butter on chicken, cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for at least 2 1/2 hours. Remove foil, brush kitchen bouquet on top of chicken and return to hot oven of 500 degrees, to brown a few minutes. Remove and serve.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: In a large bowl, add sugar to yolks, very gradually, beating constantly.
Stir in milk slowly, beating constantly; fold in the egg whites and cream.
Pour mixture into a punch bowl; chill. Garnish with nutmeg when ready to serve.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over sliced cucumbers.
Marinate in refrigerator approximately 2 hours before serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in quarters.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag and shake biscuits to coat.
Layer biscuits in bundt pan.
In a saucepan, bring margarine and brown sugar to a boil. Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: chicken fettuccine casserole
directions: Melt butter, add flour, stirring constantly.
Add milk and chicken broth and continue stirring and cook until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Put into buttered casserole and top with cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 300°.
Serves 6 to 8.
Serve with bread and salad.

title: sausage bread
directions: Let bread thaw.
Flatten on greased plate.
Spread tomato paste to edge.
Spread with onion and crumbled sausage.
Roll like jelly rolls.
Put in greased loaf pan and bake.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Spread evenly
the
first
4 ingredients in shallow pan and bake
20 minutes at 350°, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle 2/3 of this mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Then mix 10x sugar, 2 eggs, cream cheese and nuts and pour over first mixture. Bake for 1 hour or until brown on top at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Bake 2 cups recipe of corn bread.
Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add soups.
Combine crumbled corn bread and herb dressing mix.
Add soup mixture and eggs.
Add 1/2 stick melted margarine and broth.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: charlotte's salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar and shake.
Can be stored in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: cajun gumbo
directions: In 3-quart pot, boil chicken for 1/2 hour in 3 quarts of water; save broth.
In large soup pot, heat oil.
Add flour and stir until smooth and dark brown.
This is called the flare. Next, add chopped onions, garlic, pepper and green onions; saute about 5 minutes.
Add sausage, cut into pieces, and chicken flier and cut into pieces.
Saute about 20 minutes, mixing well.
Slowly mix in 3 quarts saved chicken broth and add salt and pepper sauce. Simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Fry ground meat and onions. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer until ready to serve.

title: veggie lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, stir-fry vegetables, garlic and salt in oil until crisp-tender. Spread 3/4 cup spaghetti sauce in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Arrange 7 noodles over sauce. Layer with half the vegetables, sauce and cheese. Repeat layers. Cover and bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until bubbly.

title: white hot radish pickles
directions: Pack radishes in a glass screw top quart jar.
Dissolve salt in boiling water and cool.
Add remaining ingredients to water and pour over radishes.
Close jar firmly and place in a warm room for one week.
These hot, salty and very crunchy pickles will keep in the refrigerator for 3 months.
Makes 1 pint.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat 1/2 cup sugar into egg whites; add 1/4 teaspoon salt and stir in milk slowly.
Cook in double boiler until mixture coats spoon, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add 1/8 teaspoon salt to egg whites and beat stiff.
Add remaining 1/4 cup sugar; beat well and add to custard with vanilla.
Mix thoroughly and chill 4 hours. Pile lightly in punch cups.
Sprinkle with freshly grated nutmeg. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Mix chicken, celery, green pepper, onion and avocado.
Combine mayonnaise, cayenne, salt, pepper, lemon juice and sour cream. Beat well until light and fluffy.
Pour dressing over chicken mixture.
Toss lightly.
Serve on lettuce.
Sprinkle each serving with paprika.

title: mae c. mulliner's orange baked yams
directions: Boil yams until tender.
Cool, peel and slice in 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange in greased casserole dish.
Combine other ingredients; cook over medium-high heat until hot and thick and bubbling (stirring constantly).
Pour over yams.
Bake in moderate oven until evenly hot and bubbling.
Cool for 30 minutes before serving.
(Nice with Thanksgiving turkey.)

title: fresh apple bars
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Use mixer at low speed.
Pour into greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and cover with sifted confectioners sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: italian vegetable saute
directions: Cook gently until done; will be almost dry.
Add 1 cup tomatoes cut in chunks.
Stir and cook until tomatoes are hot.

title: green chili-rice casserole
directions: Cook the rice and let cool.
Beat eggs well and slowly add oil while still beating.
Add milk to rice in casserole dish, then add egg mixture, cheese, chili, onion, parsley and seasonings.
Save a little cheese for the top.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: orange baked alaskas
directions: Scoop ice cream into 6 balls; freeze until very firm, at least 5 hours.
Cut oranges crosswise in half; cut thin slice from bottom of each half.
Cut around edges and membranes; remove fruit and membranes from orange shells.
Line bottom of each shell with fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts and line 9 x 12 x 2-inch deep dish pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Spread on crust.
Mix both pudding mixes with 2 1/2 cups milk.
Spread on cream cheese mix.
Add more Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: pastry for 2-crust pie
directions: Begin 1 hour ahead.
In medium bowl with fork, combine flour and salt.

With pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor fashion, cut in lard and shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle in cold water a tablespoon at a time, mixing lightly with fork after each addition until pastry just holds together.
With hands, shape pastry into a ball.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate about 30 minutes while making pie filling, if desired.

title: creamed dried beef
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add dried beef.
Cook slowly 5 minutes or until edges begin to curl.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Stir in milk.
Bring to boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Serve over toast.

title: fruit cake for the holiday
directions: Boil the sugar, shortening, spices, salt, dates and raisins for 15 minutes.
When cooled, add eggs, soda (dissolved in boiling water), flour, mixed fruit, cherries and nuts.
The mixture will be stiff (I use my clean hands).
Bake in greased pan in a 325° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
(I add a little brandy or rum.)

title: my country breakfast pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook sausage until done. Crumble, then drain.
Prepare pie shell. Mix cheese and sausage. Sprinkle in shell.
Lightly beat eggs in bowl. Combine remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Pour into shell.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool on a rack for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken and cool.
Separate chicken and stock.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Remove skin and fat from broth.
Add drained Veg-All, cream of chicken soup, lemon-pepper and Mrs. Dash.

title: german butter cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Use cookie press with the bar cookie design.
Then add sprinkles.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: cheryl's cabbage salad
directions: Prepare salad except noodles.
Add noodles and dressing just prior to serving.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine sugar, water, cinnamon and cloves and simmer 10 minutes.
Make 4 cups of strong tea by bringing 4 cups of water to a boil and adding 2 family size tea bags.
Steep about 10 minutes. Strain spiced sugar water and tea into large container.
Add 1 can frozen orange juice and frozen lemonade.
Add 12 cups of water.
May be refrigerated for up to one week and heated and served as needed.
If it seems too sweet, add more water.

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix all vegetables in large bowl; set aside.
Mix water, Wesson oil, sugar and vinegar well.
Pour over vegetables and let stand 24 hours.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in casserole dish.
Add salt.
Place chopped chicken over broccoli.
Pour soup over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Super quick and easy!

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Mix together crushed Oreos and 1/2 cup butter.
Pat into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Take out 1 gallon ice cream to soften while crust chills.
Spread softened ice cream on top of cookie mixture evenly.
Sprinkle peanuts over ice cream and pat down.
Put back into freezer.

title: pork chops in gravy
directions: Combine soup (undiluted), onion, worcestershire sauce , and ketchup in 2 - 3 quart casserole dish.
Put in pork chops pushing under gravy mixture.
Bake in oven at 400° for one hour.
Serve over rice.

title: corned beef barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients, except corned beef; cook until thick. Add corned beef.
Simmer together for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger bun.

title: rotel chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breast and take out bones.
Cut in cubes.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Melt cheese and butter in pan.
Add soup, Ro-Tel and chicken.
Drain spaghetti and mix well.
Pour in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hot orange dressing
directions: In 2 cup measuring cup, combine all ingredients except orange sections and almonds.
Microwave at High 1 to 2 minutes or until boiling, stirring twice.
Gently stir in oranges.
Serve with romaine or leaf lettuce.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds.
Serves 1 1/2 cups.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients along with a little regular milk. Place mixture in a large churn.
Fill rest of the way with milk.

title: corn dog squares
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a 3-quart oblong baking dish. In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, saute celery in butter or margarine for 5 minutes.
Add green onions and saute 5 minutes longer.
Transfer to a medium bowl.

title: black-eyed peas and red beans
directions: Rinse red beans; drain.
In a large saucepan, combine the red beans and 3 cups water.
Cover and let stand overnight (or use quick method).
Drain, discarding the soaking liquid.
Rinse and return beans to saucepan.
Add 3 cups fresh water, washed black-eyed peas, bay leaf and salt.
Bring to boil, reduce heat. Cover and simmer 45 to 60 minutes, or until peas and beans are tender.
Drain, discarding bay leaf.

title: crab appetizer
directions: Cream oleo well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on English muffins.
Bake for a few minutes at 450°.

title: chocolate microwave fudge
directions: Mix in microwavable bowl (deep).
Cook on High for 4 minutes. Take out and stir well.
Put back in for 5 minutes.
Bring out and stir in 1 cup of chocolate chips and 10 large marshmallows.
Pour in greased pan.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and salad oil together.
Add well beaten eggs and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and stir in.
Mix until smooth, add chopped pecans, pineapple and grated carrots.
Bake in two or three 9-inch or oblong cake pans at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: easy salisbury steak
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly beef, onion, bread crumbs, egg white and garlic.
Firmly shape into 6 oval patties.
Spray 10-inch skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Over medium high heat, cook 3 patties at a time until browned on both sides. Remove patties and set aside.
Stir in gravy and mushrooms.
Heat to boiling.
Return patties to skillet.
Reduce heat to low. Cover, simmer 20 minutes or until done, stirring occasionally. Serve over hot noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: south seas beef and vegetables
directions: Brown meat in hot oil.
Drain pineapple and add syrup to skillet with soy sauce and vinegar.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cook 15 minutes.
Add pineapple and vegetables.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Combine cornstarch and water.
Stir until smooth.
Add slowly to beef mixture.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil, while stirring gently.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken salad lettuce wraps(easy appetizer)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Bake almonds for 5 to 7 minutes or until toasted. In a small bowl, stir chicken salad, cranberries and almonds together. If necessary, cut the bottom of each butterhead leaf, making leaves about 6-inches long. Discard bottom of leaves. Spread about 3 tablespoons of mixture lengthwise down one edge of each butterhead leaf. Roll up and secure each with 3 wooden cocktail picks, completely enclosing salad in lettuce. Use a gentle sawing motion to cut each lettuce roll between the picks, making 3 pieces.

title: pumpkin-peanut butter soup
directions: Saute celery
and
onion
in butter or oleo.
Add flour and stir until slightly browned.
Add chicken broth, pumpkin, peanut butter,
milk,
salt
and
pepper.	Let come to rolling boil and serve.
Makes 1 quart.

title: seasoned oven baked potatoes
directions: Bake in a pan lined with foil; butter the pan.
Wash and slice potatoes, leaving skin on potatoes.
Make a layer of potatoes, then put peppers and onions on top of potatoes.
Put butter on top. Next sprinkle with salt, garlic salt, and black and red pepper as desired.
Layer as many as you want to cook.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour, then turn oven off and finish cooking while oven cools down.

title: special chicken
directions: Combine stuffing mix, oleo and water.
Toss until moist.
Put half of mixture in a greased baking dish.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in flour.
Pour mixture into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Top with 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with Dorito chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts together and form into a ball. Roll in nuts.
Refrigerate.
Helps to refrigerate before forming into a ball for ease of handling.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Cream well.
Add sifted dry ingredients (except the powdered sugar).
Drop by teaspoons on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325°
for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and sift powdered sugar over while still warm.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart microwave casserole dish. Mix well, making sure brown sugar and onion soup mix are dissolved.
Cover and cook on High temperature for 7 minutes. Stir beans and cook on High temperature for 7 more minutes. Serves 6.

title: mazetti
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown hamburger and add to noodles. Saute onion and celery in butter until tender and add to noodles and hamburger.
Stir in rest of ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole.
Top with slices of Velveeta cheese. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly coat 16 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pans with oil spray.
Mix flour, corn meal, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir in milk, oil and eggs until all are moistened. Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in centers comes out clean.
Let muffins cool in pan for 10 minutes before turning out.

title: buttermilk bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm water.
Mix the hot water with the honey and add the buttermilk.
The temperature should be just slightly warm.
Stir the flour and salt together, making a well in the center.

Pour the yeast and buttermilk mixture into the well and stir from the center outwards, incorporating all the flour. Test the dough to see whether more flour or more water is needed and adjust accordingly.
The bread is lightest if the dough is slightly soft.
For rolls, it should be quite soft.
Knead about 20 minutes, adding the butter in cold bits at the end of the kneading time.
Form the dough into a ball and place it smooth side up in the bowl.
Cover and keep in a warm draft free place.
After about an hour and a half, gently poke the center of the dough about 1/2 inch deep with your wet finger.
If the hole doesn't fill in at all or if the dough sighs it is ready for the next step.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Heat oleo, cocoa and milk
in saucepan until starts to bubble. Remove from heat. Add confectioners sugar, vanilla and chopped nuts. Stir and pour over hot cake while it is still in the pan. Cut and serve.

title: spaghetti and white clam sauce
directions: Heat the oil and butter in a skillet.
Add garlic and shallots and cook until lightly browned.
Add the parsley, clam juice and wine.
Also add salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and let simmer for fifteen minutes.
Add the clams and cook five more minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.
May serve with hot pepper flakes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time to creamed mixture, beating well after each egg.
Add flour (about 2 tablespoons at a time).
Beat in vanilla.
Spoon into greased and lightly floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Check oven after 45 minutes; don't let it dry out.
Can be frozen and thawed.

title: creamy chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar, cocoa and vanilla, mixing with electric mixer until well blended.
Blend in eggs; pour into crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: best fried pies
directions: Mix ingredients well and let stand 2 hours, covered with cloth, or may be left overnight in refrigerator.
Using a walnut size piece of dough, roll and cut the size of a saucer.
Fill with favorite pie filling.
Close by folding in half and seal.
Fry in Crisco vegetable shortening (solid shortening) until golden brown. Dust with powdered sugar (optional).

title: pioneer rice pudding
directions: Measure ingredients in order given in a bowl.
Beat vigorously.
Bake in well-greased loaf tin at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: cheezy potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes a little.
Mix together the remaining ingredients; put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with topping.

title: justin's potato soup
directions: Cook the potatoes, chicken broth and onion until potatoes are soft. Add evaporated milk.
Thicken with flour or cornstarch and water.

title: champagne salad
directions: Soften and blend cream cheese and sugar.
Mix pineapple, fruit and nuts.
Add whipped topping. Combine with cheese mixture. Place in an oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze for several hours or overnight.
Does do nicely over longer period.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: grille shrimp with cream sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add bay leaf, worcestershire sauce, wine and lemon.
Allow to cook and reduce down by half.
In a separate skillet, saute 1/2 onion in oil until transparent.
Add shrimp and toss in skillet with oil, onion and Cajun seasoning.
Remove from heat when cooked.
After sauce has reduced, stir in butter and heavy cream.
Allow to heat and cook through a minute or two.
Add shrimp, stir together and serve.

title: pebernodder
directions: *Break pods; remove seeds and crush them with wooden spoon (use 1 1/2 to 2 teaspoons of crushed seed).

title: strawberry crunch
directions: Mix gelatin and water until dissolved.
Add fruit and blend. Then add nuts. Pour 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill for 1 hour.
Reserve remaining mixture at room temperature. After bottom of mixture is set, spread with yogurt.
Top with remaining gelatin.
Chill until firm.
Serves 12.
Each Serving Size:
1 portion.
Exchanges:
1 fruit and 1/2 fat.
Calories: 84.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus, cheese and eggs in casserole dish.
Put can of mushroom soup or 1 cup of white sauce over all.
Top with bread crumbs or put some cheese on top.
Bake until it bubbles.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Spread on flat side of one cooled cookie.
Top with a second cookie.
Variation:
Substitute 3/4 cup pumpkin for cocoa, add 1/2 c. more flour.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat 1/3 cup sugar into egg yolks. Add salt. Stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon. Cool.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all together and form into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: mud pie
directions: Mix flour, nuts and melted margarine.
Place in an oblong cake pan and pat down.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and one 16 ounce container Cool Whip together. Pour over cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Spread the other 16 ounces Cool Whip over pudding layer.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Then top with bacon and bake for 15 to 20 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger rice pie
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, 1 teaspoon salt, oregano, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce; mix well.
Pat mixture firmly over bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate; pinch flutings around edge and set aside.
Combine rice, water, 1/4 cup cheese, remaining tomato sauce and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Pour into meat shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, then sprinkle on remaining cheese.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into wedges.

title: crab or shrimp dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, salt, cayenne pepper, lemon juice and the cream cheese.
Soften with fork; mix well.
Add other ingredients.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butterscotch morsels over hot (not boiling) water; add 1/4 cup butter and melt it.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup light brown sugar, packed. Cool 5 minutes and then stir in eggs, vanilla and flour sifted with baking powder and salt.
Stir in nuts and bake in 350° oven.

title: quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Beat eggs, biscuit mix, butter or oleo, milk, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into a 9-inch or bigger pie plate or oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle bacon and cheese over top.
Press gently.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cocoa sauce or syrup
directions: Cook cocoa, sugar, salt, corn syrup and milk together.
Slowly cook until it is at the boiling stage.
Remove and add vanilla and butter.
Makes 2 cups.

title: original banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in the top of a double boiler. Stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until thickened.

title: beefy bean burritos
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet or pan and drain fat.
Add 1/2 taco seasoning mix and 1/2 cup water.
Add mashed pinto beans. Stir and cook over low heat until heated through.
Heat flour tortillas in a separate skillet on stove until soft or in microwave for 30 seconds.
Fill tortillas with beef mixture, grated cheese, chopped tomatoes, shredded lettuce, and taco sauce. Makes 10-12 burritos.

title: graham cracker brownies
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Combine sugar, salt, graham cracker crumbs and nuts; add to beaten eggs, mixing well.
Add vanilla. Spread mixture evenly in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut while still warm.
They can be served as a pudding with a topping of ice cream or whipped cream, or can be dusted with confectioners sugar and served as brownies.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and boil 1 minute.
Then cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Chill dressing and vegetables before mixing together.
Will keep refrigerated several days.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine raisins and boiling water; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat shortening, butter or margarine (whichever you use), sugar, salt, spices and eggs until creamy and fluffy.
Scrape bowl often.
Blend in the applesauce, then the flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add the raisins to the mixture and mix well.

title: cindy's broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Cook broccoli as package directs. Combine all ingredients together in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese cake tarts
directions: Line cupcake pans with muffin papers.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in each cup.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Divide among the muffin papers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Top with pie filling.
Makes 24 tarts.

title: quick spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onion and garlic, chopped.
Remove from skillet.
Brown Italian sausage; cut in 1-inch pieces.
Return onion and garlic to skillet.
Add spices and tomatoes.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes. Serve over spaghetti.
Add black olives for color.

title: seafood dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with pita or bagel chips.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water and pineapple juice.
Let partially set.
Add diced pineapple, salad dressing, marshmallows and Cheddar cheese.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Stir milk into mayonnaise slowly, stirring constantly.
Mix this into the hot jello.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Chill.

title: lemon broccoli
directions: In a vegetable steamer, steam the broccoli until just tender when tested with a knife, 3 to 5 minutes.

title: cranberry apple crunch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 1 minute.
Add cranberries and boil 2 minutes longer; add apples.
Put in casserole or other flat baking dish.
Combine dry ingredients; add margarine.
Mix until crumbly. Sprinkle over fruit mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.
Serves 4.

title: ice pack cookies
directions: May use 1/2 package dates and 1 cup nuts.
Make in rolls and leave in icebox 24 hours.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix soup and milk well; add vegetables and chicken and mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, water chestnuts, cheese and mayonnaise together and pour into casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers and margarine.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (approximately 30 minutes).

title: shrimp, avocado, fruit salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir, cover and chill.
Melt margarine; spread on both sides of bread.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Arrange on 4 salad plates.
Divide lettuce; put on top of bread slices.
Arrange grapefruit sections, avocado, onion slices and shrimp on salad leaves.
Drizzle honey dressing over. Bread may be served separately.

title: schoharie autumn stew
directions: Brown meat in oil in pan.
Bring water to boil in large pot. Add vegetables, meat and seasonings.
Turn down to low to simmer. Cover pot; stir occasionally for 2 hours, approximately or until meat is tender.
Mix cream of tartar in cold water; add slowly and stir to desired consistency.
Serve hot with coffee and corn bread!!

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine Veg-All, corn, onion, mayonnaise and cheese. Pour into baking dish. Top with crushed crackers and melted butter. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: punch cake
directions: Bake cake in layers or loaf, 13 x 9-inch.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Punch holes in cake 1 1/2 inches apart.
Pour jello over while cake is hot.
Cool cake or chill cake in refrigerator night before making frosting.
Beat instant pudding with 1 cup cold milk according to directions.
Add Cool Whip; fold in.
Frost cake and chill.

title: holiday wreath salad
directions: Mix jello with one cup boiling water.
Beat with mixer until frothy.
Fold in sour cream.
Mix well.
Add cherries and pineapple.
Pour into 1 1/2 or 2-quart mold and chill overnight.

title: peanut butter-butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add milk until freezer is 2/3 full and freeze.

title: pineapple chicken chow mein
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add onions, celery, bean sprouts, drained pineapple, bouillon cubes dissolved in water, salt, pepper and brown sugar.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Mix cornstarch with soy sauce.
Stir in vegetable mixture.
Add cooked, cubed chicken and cook, stirring, for 5 minutes.
Serve over chow mein noodles or rice.

title: barbecued corn on the cob
directions: Melt butter, add ingredients (except corn), stir and mix well. Place 1 ear of corn onto foil wrapper, brush sauce onto corn. Wrap corn and twist the ends. You can double wrap corn, if desired.
Do each corn.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes, or grill, turning often, for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage cornbread squares
directions: Prepare muffin mix according to package directions, except using the egg, milk and mustard.
Mix until moistened.
Stir in corn and spoon into greased 9-inch pan.
Place sausage 1 inch apart on top of mixture and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: danish meat balls
directions: Have the beef and pork ground twice.
Combine with flour, salt, pepper, onion, eggs and milk; mix well.
Shape into 3/4 to 1-inch meat balls.
Fry in butter or margarine.
This may be made into a meat loaf.
Bake at 370° until it pulls away from pan.
This goes well with fried red cabbage.

title: sausage succotash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine sausage, lima beans, potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese, 1/2 can onions, soup, milk, corn and seasoned salt.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: garlic-dill pickles(cold packed)
directions: Wash and dry cucumbers.
Place in crock with spices, except what is used to boil (for brine).
Boil water, salt and vinegar. Let cool to room temperature, then pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 2 to 4 weeks.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Remove skin and finely shred the smoked salmon.
Add softened cream cheese in small chunks.
Process all ingredients in a food processor.	Pepper to taste.
Enjoy on crackers, bagels or bread.

title: elf cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Pour in graham cracker crumbs and smooth evenly.
Add layer of chocolate chips. Evenly spread a coconut layer, then butterscotch chips.
Top with layer of nuts.
Pour milk over top and bake at 350° until light brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool, then cut in squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done, reserving liquid.
Cook egg noodles in reserved liquid.
Remove chicken meat from the bone; add to noodles in small pieces.
Stir in one stick of margarine and can of soup.
Salt according to taste.
Pour into a large 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt one stick of margarine and combine with stuffing.
Sprinkle over top of noodle mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: zucchini fritti or fried squash
directions: Wash and scrape zucchini lightly.
Cut crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Fry in hot oil about 3 minutes or until slightly brown and soft.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; also sprinkle each slice with chopped parsley and grated cheese.
Serve hot.
Serves six to eight.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Prepare 1 large can of pumpkin according to directions for pie filling.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Cut 1 1/2 sticks of margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip, whipping cream or ice cream.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix
cinnamon
and 5 tablespoons sugar; set aside.
Cut apples into
slices.
Beat
eggs with 1 1/2 cups sugar and oil until smooth
and fluffy.
Mix in flour, baking powder, salt, orange juice
and vanilla.
Grease a tube pan.
Layer batter, apples, then sugar and cinnamon mixture. Repeat 3 times.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and mango; drain.
Boil noodles until tender; drain.
Combine ground beef mixture and all three cans of soup.
Simmer for ten minutes, stirring often.
Add to noodles. Stir and spread in large casserole dish or pan.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.

title: salit
directions: Cut all in small bite size.
Mix well.
Let stand overnight. Put in sealable container and refrigerate until used up.

title: cornmeal waffles
directions: Combine peach filling, lemon juice and ground cinnamon in a small saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring often, until thoroughly heated.
Spoon over waffles and sprinkle with almonds, if desired.
Yield:
1 3/4 cups.

title: barleycorn's canadian cheese soup
directions: Melt butter. Stir-fry vegetables until transparent. Add flour, then water.
Mix in cheese and simmer until mixture reaches soup consistency. Should be smooth.

title: chip dip
directions: Mix cream cheese into buttermilk and add remaining ingredients.
Whip until well blended with mixer.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Bake in lightly greased 9 x 12-inch pan in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
When cool, ice with Pistachio Icing.

title: swiss steak
directions: In heavy skillet, cook onion and green pepper in fat until tender. Then take the beef and pound flour into it with the edge of a heavy plate. Brown meat on both sides in the fat. Then add the tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, water, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: vermicelli greek salad
directions: Cook vermicelli per package directions.
Drain and rinse in cool water.
Mix with oil, lemon juice and Greek seasoning. Marinate overnight or at least 4 hours.
Chop black olives, green onions and pimento.
Mix with vermicelli and chill.

title: betty lou's pecan toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to moderate (350°).
Grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Beat together butter and sugar in large mixer bowl until well mixed.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour until well blended.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Cover and set aside. Cook onions and green pepper in butter.
Add Cheez Whiz and soup. Put in pan and heat thoroughly.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In large saucepan, cook sugar, syrup and water to hard ball stage.
Add peanuts and cook until golden brown.
Add butter and vanilla; stir until well mixed.
Add soda and stir well.
(Do not stir too long after adding soda.)
Pour into a buttered pan. Yields approximately 2 pounds.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef, seasoned salt and onion in skillet.
Prepare mashed potatoes to taste.
Then warm corn in a 9 x 13-inch casserole bowl.
Layer ground beef, cheese, corn and potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Cook at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: spritz(cookies)
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add egg and vanilla. Sift flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Put through cookie press on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° just until edges turn a light brownish color.

title: cincinnati milling machine pecan pie
directions: Beat together sugar, salt and eggs on high speed and then add melted butter and the vanilla and beat real good.
Next, add the syrup and mix real well.
Put the chopped nuts in the bottom of the pie shell and pour in the filling and bake for 1 hour on the bottom rack at 300° or longer depending upon whether filling is set up.

title: lo-cal drink
directions: Steep tea bag in boiling hot water for 2 minutes.
Place 3 cubes in each 10 ounce glass (2).
Remove tea bag and add remaining ingredients.
Stir briskly and pour into glasses over the cubes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Place cinnamon sticks, allspice, and cloves in cheesecloth bag.
Place water and spice bag in sauce pan, bring to a boil. Remove from heat, add tea bags and steep for 5 minutes.
Discard tea bags and spice bag.
